1
00:00:00,507 --> 00:00:03,946
(One day in April with spring in the air)

2
00:00:03,947 --> 00:00:05,146
Gosh. Then what do I do?

3
00:00:05,147 --> 00:00:06,346
- What's going on?
- I'm in trouble.

4
00:00:06,347 --> 00:00:07,987
- You're telling me not to do that?
- Don't do that.

5
00:00:08,012 --> 00:00:09,082
What's going on?

6
00:00:09,107 --> 00:00:10,107
- Kyung Hoon, - What's going on?

7
00:00:10,149 --> 00:00:11,978
you're sitting in the royal, special seat.

8
00:00:11,979 --> 00:00:14,578
- This is my seat now.
- Your wife even changed our seats?

9
00:00:14,579 --> 00:00:16,048
- Yes, to make sure I stand out.
- My gosh. The two of them...

10
00:00:16,049 --> 00:00:17,088
- He took Ho Dong's seat.
- Really?

11
00:00:17,089 --> 00:00:19,318
- Goodness. You sit over there.
- He took Ho Dong's seat.

12
00:00:19,319 --> 00:00:22,528
- Soo Geun, can't you read the room?
- What do you mean?

13
00:00:22,529 --> 00:00:24,528
They're having a serious conversation.

14
00:00:24,529 --> 00:00:26,098
Is there something that worries you?

15
00:00:26,099 --> 00:00:27,399
One of my acquaintances...

16
00:00:27,959 --> 00:00:29,628
got married and had a baby.

17
00:00:29,629 --> 00:00:31,168
And both of the couple work.

18
00:00:31,169 --> 00:00:33,998
So it's hard to look after their baby, apparently.

19
00:00:33,999 --> 00:00:35,508
- It's hard for dual-income couples.
- Yes.

20
00:00:35,509 --> 00:00:37,968
So he vented to me about it.

21
00:00:37,969 --> 00:00:39,638
And that could easily happen to me or Kyung Hoon.

22
00:00:39,639 --> 00:00:42,278
Hey, where does your friend live?

23
00:00:42,279 --> 00:00:43,708
He lives in Paju.

24
00:00:43,709 --> 00:00:45,048
- Paju?
- In Gyeonggi Province... Yes.

25
00:00:45,049 --> 00:00:46,978
If he lives in Paju, he doesn't have to worry.

26
00:00:46,979 --> 00:00:49,548
Gyeonggi Province offers a family care support program.

27
00:00:49,549 --> 00:00:50,788
He gives people advice on his show for a reason.

28
00:00:50,789 --> 00:00:51,818
Haven't you watched the news?

29
00:00:51,819 --> 00:00:53,418
I think I heard about that program on the news.

30
00:00:53,419 --> 00:00:55,388
- He already looked into that.
- That's right.

31
00:00:55,389 --> 00:00:57,358
Right. A family with a child...

32
00:00:57,359 --> 00:00:59,198
faces times when both parents are unable to look after their child.

33
00:00:59,199 --> 00:01:01,158
The key benefit of this program is this.

34
00:01:01,159 --> 00:01:04,069
If relatives like your parents or neighbors look after the child,

35
00:01:04,469 --> 00:01:05,698
you're eligible for the family care subsidy.

36
00:01:05,699 --> 00:01:07,098
- The family care subsidy?
- Family members also... Yes.

37
00:01:07,099 --> 00:01:08,509
- Family members too?
- Yes.

38
00:01:09,281 --> 00:01:12,891
Depending on the number of children you have,

39
00:01:13,279 --> 00:01:14,808
the amount of the subsidy varies. Is that right?

40
00:01:14,809 --> 00:01:15,809
- Yes.
- That's amazing.

41
00:01:15,810 --> 00:01:18,978
- Right?
- We had no idea there was...

42
00:01:18,979 --> 00:01:20,518
- such a practical program.
- That's right.

43
00:01:20,519 --> 00:01:22,448
Sang Min, you should let your friend know...

44
00:01:22,449 --> 00:01:24,288
- about the program. Yes.
- I should tell him.

45
00:01:24,289 --> 00:01:26,918
I'm from Yangpyeong. I should have another baby.

46
00:01:26,919 --> 00:01:27,919
Let's go, Ho Dong.

47
00:01:29,889 --> 00:01:31,028
Look at Jang Hoon's face.

48
00:01:31,029 --> 00:01:32,228
Let's have another baby.

49
00:01:32,229 --> 00:01:34,629
Let's all live in Gyeonggi Province.

50
00:01:35,269 --> 00:01:39,768
Gyeonggi Province has long been providing food and necessities...

51
00:01:39,769 --> 00:01:42,068
to any residents in the province...

52
00:01:42,069 --> 00:01:44,838
- who are struggling financially.
- That's right.

53
00:01:44,839 --> 00:01:45,908
- Right.
- The project is called Just Dream.

54
00:01:45,909 --> 00:01:48,178
- Right, "Just Dream."
- It's "dream" as in wish and hope.

55
00:01:48,179 --> 00:01:49,179
- Right.
- Just Dream.

56
00:01:49,180 --> 00:01:50,478
- You didn't know there were...
- It also means...

57
00:01:50,479 --> 00:01:51,778
- many different policies...
- what you see in sleep.

58
00:01:51,779 --> 00:01:53,448
- for those in need, did you?
- I didn't know.

59
00:01:53,449 --> 00:01:54,748
- Exactly.
- Right.

60
00:01:54,749 --> 00:01:55,918
If you don't know, you miss all the benefits.

61
00:01:55,919 --> 00:01:56,919
You miss all of them.

62
00:01:57,135 --> 00:01:58,145
- What?
- What?

63
00:01:58,841 --> 00:01:59,841
- What?
- What?

64
00:02:00,889 --> 00:02:03,029
- Wait. The teacher is here?
- The teacher?

65
00:02:03,929 --> 00:02:05,328
- Why...
- Hello, sir.

66
00:02:05,329 --> 00:02:06,329
A real teacher is here.

67
00:02:06,330 --> 00:02:07,798
- A real teacher is here.
- What's that back there?

68
00:02:07,799 --> 00:02:09,828
- He seems... Is he upset?
- What?

69
00:02:09,829 --> 00:02:10,829
Wait.

70
00:02:10,869 --> 00:02:12,138
- What is this?
- What's going on?

71
00:02:12,139 --> 00:02:14,569
All rise for the King.

72
00:02:15,475 --> 00:02:16,775
The "King" is here?

73
00:02:17,509 --> 00:02:18,909
- Oh, my goodness.
- What?

74
00:02:19,439 --> 00:02:21,508
My goodness. The King is here.

75
00:02:21,509 --> 00:02:23,679
- Look who's at the door.
- Oh, my.

76
00:02:24,149 --> 00:02:27,018
- Your Majesty.
- I'm surprised.

77
00:02:27,019 --> 00:02:30,219
- This is the return of the kings.
- Right.

78
00:02:31,089 --> 00:02:32,658
So we have two kings here.

79
00:02:32,659 --> 00:02:34,188
And is he a eunuch?

80
00:02:34,189 --> 00:02:35,659
Are you the kings' warden?

81
00:02:36,089 --> 00:02:37,729
I am the kings' warden.

82
00:02:38,289 --> 00:02:40,029
It's nice to meet you all. We are...

83
00:02:40,399 --> 00:02:44,629
from Closely Connected To Danjong The Tragic King High School.

84
00:02:44,842 --> 00:02:46,252
I'm Seol Min Seok. I study history.

85
00:02:46,899 --> 00:02:48,939
Hi. I am...

86
00:02:49,471 --> 00:02:52,470
Lee Min Woo, an actor with 46 years of experience. Nice to meet you.

87
00:02:52,495 --> 00:02:54,135
That's longer than even the oldest Ballantine's.

88
00:02:55,379 --> 00:02:56,749
Hi, everyone.

89
00:02:57,209 --> 00:02:59,418
I played Danjong twice. I'm Jung Tae Woo.

90
00:02:59,419 --> 00:03:01,249
Oh, my. He played Danjong twice, not just once?

91
00:03:01,419 --> 00:03:03,318
(The Kings are here at Brother School.)

92
00:03:03,319 --> 00:03:05,358
- I feel like I should be solemn.
- That's amazing.

93
00:03:05,359 --> 00:03:06,888
- It's a little bit...
- Come to think of it,

94
00:03:06,889 --> 00:03:09,258
- they're the original Danjongs.
- Right.

95
00:03:09,259 --> 00:03:11,658
- He's a famous history instructor.
- That's right.

96
00:03:11,659 --> 00:03:14,128
- I really wanted to meet you.
- Exactly.

97
00:03:14,129 --> 00:03:15,168
- Mr. Seol.
- I mean it.

98
00:03:15,169 --> 00:03:18,598
Min Seok, do you know any of us?

99
00:03:18,599 --> 00:03:22,168
I've never met any of you before.

100
00:03:22,169 --> 00:03:23,468
- None of us?
- Never?

101
00:03:23,469 --> 00:03:25,778
- None of us likes studying.
- I've never met him before.

102
00:03:25,779 --> 00:03:27,538
- I've only seen him on TV.
- I've never met him before.

103
00:03:27,539 --> 00:03:28,549
What about you, Min Woo?

104
00:03:28,849 --> 00:03:30,809
- I have met Ho Dong before.
- Ho Dong?

105
00:03:30,979 --> 00:03:32,349
He scolded me 19 years ago.

106
00:03:32,679 --> 00:03:33,818
(Is he another victim of Ho Dong?)

107
00:03:33,819 --> 00:03:35,588
- Nineteen years ago?
- He even beat up a king too?

108
00:03:35,589 --> 00:03:37,218
That's not true. What are you talking about?

109
00:03:37,219 --> 00:03:39,388
- The man who beats a king up.
- Im Kkeok Jeong.

110
00:03:39,389 --> 00:03:40,618
- The man who beats a king up.
- Han Myong Hoe.

111
00:03:40,619 --> 00:03:43,058
- We were recording a show.
- Yes.

112
00:03:43,059 --> 00:03:46,029
I was telling a story, and suddenly...

113
00:03:46,329 --> 00:03:48,869
Ho Dong suddenly said, "Min Woo!"

114
00:03:49,299 --> 00:03:51,068
"Speak a little faster, please."

115
00:03:51,069 --> 00:03:53,398
"People will switch the channel at this rate."

116
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:55,238
- That's what he said.
- I see. My goodness.

117
00:03:55,239 --> 00:03:56,668
Were we shooting "Ya Shim Man Man?"

118
00:03:56,669 --> 00:03:58,108
- Maybe "Strong Heart."
- Yes, it was "Strong Heart."

119
00:03:58,109 --> 00:03:59,708
- We were shooting "Strong Heart?"
- Yes.

120
00:03:59,709 --> 00:04:01,748
And after that, he never spoke to me.

121
00:04:01,749 --> 00:04:03,708
- My gosh.
- This must be a real story.

122
00:04:03,709 --> 00:04:05,148
- That's not true.
- This must be a real story.

123
00:04:05,149 --> 00:04:06,519
- You're lying.
- Goodbye.

124
00:04:06,719 --> 00:04:09,918
(Should auld acquaintance be forgot?)

125
00:04:09,919 --> 00:04:12,058
- Goodbye, everyone!
- I mean...

126
00:04:12,059 --> 00:04:14,159
- Is speaking slowly that bad?
- He didn't give you a chance.

127
00:04:14,619 --> 00:04:16,958
- He speaks much faster now.
- Is speaking slowly...

128
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:18,898
- Did he really say those things?
- He used to...

129
00:04:18,899 --> 00:04:21,258
- Yes, he did.
- He used to speak like an old man,

130
00:04:21,259 --> 00:04:22,969
and he was such a boomer.

131
00:04:23,199 --> 00:04:24,199
- He's improved a lot as a person.
- True.

132
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:25,398
- Is this him speaking faster?
- He used to speak more slowly?

133
00:04:25,399 --> 00:04:27,638
I guess I volunteered to play the villain...

134
00:04:27,639 --> 00:04:28,808
to help you build your character.

135
00:04:28,809 --> 00:04:30,238
That's what happened. Right.

136
00:04:30,239 --> 00:04:32,738
If that's the case, why didn't you let me talk for six hours?

137
00:04:32,739 --> 00:04:34,638
- For six hours?
- That's so mean.

138
00:04:34,639 --> 00:04:36,278
- For six straight hours?
- Oh, gosh.

139
00:04:36,279 --> 00:04:37,448
(Ho Dong's Victims' Association is nowhere and everywhere at once.)

140
00:04:37,449 --> 00:04:38,548
- This must be a real story.
- Is that right?

141
00:04:38,549 --> 00:04:40,978
I guess the other guests were doing such a great job.

142
00:04:40,979 --> 00:04:43,918
- I guess they did such a great job.
- I knew it.

143
00:04:43,919 --> 00:04:45,358
Because you seemed tired,

144
00:04:45,359 --> 00:04:47,158
I was just trying to look out for you.

145
00:04:47,159 --> 00:04:48,318
- In that case...
- By the way,

146
00:04:48,319 --> 00:04:50,459
Min Seok looks...

147
00:04:50,589 --> 00:04:52,358
much younger than his age.

148
00:04:52,359 --> 00:04:53,598
- But he's actually...
- He is young.

149
00:04:53,599 --> 00:04:55,868
- the same age as Ho Dong.
- Nonsense.

150
00:04:55,869 --> 00:04:58,798
- Is that true?
- That means Ho Dong let himself go.

151
00:04:58,799 --> 00:05:00,038
- Am I right?
- Oh, that's right.

152
00:05:00,039 --> 00:05:01,269
- Are you serious?
- He's the same age as Ho Dong?

153
00:05:01,439 --> 00:05:02,439
It's nice to meet you, my friend.

154
00:05:03,439 --> 00:05:04,439
It's nice to meet you.

155
00:05:04,739 --> 00:05:05,739
It's nice to meet you, my friend.

156
00:05:06,739 --> 00:05:08,409
It's nice to meet you.

157
00:05:08,909 --> 00:05:09,909
That's weird.

158
00:05:09,910 --> 00:05:12,248
- But he's a teacher.
- Really?

159
00:05:12,249 --> 00:05:13,518
(They were both born in 1970, but they look different.)

160
00:05:13,519 --> 00:05:15,588
- Is it... Is it true?
- Are you serious?

161
00:05:15,589 --> 00:05:17,248
- Exactly.
- He was born in 1970?

162
00:05:17,249 --> 00:05:18,718
I can't believe he's older than me.

163
00:05:18,719 --> 00:05:20,018
I have a baby face,

164
00:05:20,019 --> 00:05:22,059
and you have such a baby face.

165
00:05:22,259 --> 00:05:24,188
- Seriously.
- Which one is weird, then?

166
00:05:24,189 --> 00:05:25,958
- That's amazing.
- I do have a baby face.

167
00:05:25,959 --> 00:05:27,098
Min Seok has been doing a great job taking care of himself.

168
00:05:27,099 --> 00:05:28,698
He has thick, dark eyebrows too.

169
00:05:28,699 --> 00:05:29,968
- He was born with a baby face.
- I had no idea.

170
00:05:29,969 --> 00:05:31,938
- I have a baby face too.
- Ho Dong has...

171
00:05:31,939 --> 00:05:33,799
- a round face.
- He has a round face.

172
00:05:33,939 --> 00:05:34,968
A round face.

173
00:05:34,969 --> 00:05:36,168
- Right. He has a round face.
- I'm so amazed...

174
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:37,338
He looks way younger than his age.

175
00:05:37,339 --> 00:05:39,139
What's your favorite sport?

176
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:42,079
Actually, I'm often asked a question like that.

177
00:05:42,679 --> 00:05:45,218
But I believe it's better to avoid one unhealthy habit...

178
00:05:45,219 --> 00:05:47,518
than to do ten healthy things.

179
00:05:47,519 --> 00:05:50,249
He doesn't sound like someone who's young.

180
00:05:52,859 --> 00:05:54,718
- His tone suits his age.
- Right?

181
00:05:54,719 --> 00:05:56,988
- He sounds like someone at his age.
- Even older than that.

182
00:05:56,989 --> 00:05:58,928
His face looks way younger than his actual age.

183
00:05:58,929 --> 00:06:00,928
But his tone gives away that he's in his mid-50s.

184
00:06:00,929 --> 00:06:02,968
- His voice doesn't sound young.
- Right.

185
00:06:02,969 --> 00:06:04,528
- "I believe it's better..."
- Right.

186
00:06:04,529 --> 00:06:05,799
- His voice doesn't sound so young.
- Exactly.

187
00:06:06,069 --> 00:06:07,069
- By the way, - What do you call that?

188
00:06:07,070 --> 00:06:10,008
do the three of you know one another?

189
00:06:10,009 --> 00:06:11,878
Min Woo and Tae Woo must be acquainted.

190
00:06:11,879 --> 00:06:12,938
- Both of them are actors.
- Exactly.

191
00:06:12,939 --> 00:06:14,838
- Yes, we know each other well.
- We know each other well.

192
00:06:14,839 --> 00:06:16,648
When I was six years old,

193
00:06:16,649 --> 00:06:18,278
I saw Min Woo for the first time.

194
00:06:18,279 --> 00:06:20,379
- Oh, my. You remember that?
- A production team...

195
00:06:20,919 --> 00:06:21,988
came to my neighborhood.

196
00:06:21,989 --> 00:06:24,788
Back then, it was rare...

197
00:06:24,789 --> 00:06:26,758
to see a show being filmed.

198
00:06:26,759 --> 00:06:28,459
- So a large crowd flocked there.
- He has great vocal projection.

199
00:06:28,589 --> 00:06:29,889
I was watching it.

200
00:06:30,259 --> 00:06:31,958
And I saw Min Woo acting.

201
00:06:31,959 --> 00:06:34,958
He looked so fascinating and cool.

202
00:06:34,959 --> 00:06:37,329
I think that was the first time...

203
00:06:37,629 --> 00:06:39,699
I had ever dreamed of appearing on TV.

204
00:06:39,939 --> 00:06:42,968
Back then, I was quite good-looking.

205
00:06:42,969 --> 00:06:45,709
So the director gave me his business card.

206
00:06:46,039 --> 00:06:47,378
He told me to come for an audition.

207
00:06:47,379 --> 00:06:49,479
And I passed the audition.

208
00:06:49,709 --> 00:06:50,808
It was when I was a little kid.

209
00:06:50,809 --> 00:06:53,279
Min Woo must have the most acting experience.

210
00:06:54,149 --> 00:06:55,388
- Right.
- Min Woo,

211
00:06:55,389 --> 00:06:56,649
in what year did you debut?

212
00:06:57,089 --> 00:06:58,089
In 1980.

213
00:06:58,519 --> 00:07:00,419
- In 1980?
- Back then...

214
00:07:00,519 --> 00:07:02,728
- That's interesting.
- That was even before I was born.

215
00:07:02,729 --> 00:07:04,888
Did you debut back when TV was still in black and white?

216
00:07:04,889 --> 00:07:06,258
- No, TV was in color then.
- How old were you when you debuted?

217
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:07,259
- TV was in color?
- How old?

218
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:08,428
- How old were you then?
- How old were you?

219
00:07:08,429 --> 00:07:10,168
- I was 4 years old.
- You debuted at the age of 4.

220
00:07:10,169 --> 00:07:11,229
- I was four years old.
- Back then...

221
00:07:11,499 --> 00:07:14,638
I was walking down the street in Chungmuro...

222
00:07:14,639 --> 00:07:16,938
when a modeling agent scouted me, thinking I was a girl.

223
00:07:16,939 --> 00:07:18,008
On the street?

224
00:07:18,009 --> 00:07:20,879
Yes, he scouted me on the street. I guess...

225
00:07:21,239 --> 00:07:25,078
the first private boat in Korea was launched around that time.

226
00:07:25,079 --> 00:07:27,749
I started my career modeling for a promotional leaflet.

227
00:07:28,179 --> 00:07:29,188
- I acted in my first drama later.
- In 1980.

228
00:07:29,189 --> 00:07:30,248
That was 1980.

229
00:07:30,249 --> 00:07:32,058
Since they played a king,

230
00:07:32,059 --> 00:07:34,258
- they can join our school...
- No.

231
00:07:34,259 --> 00:07:36,588
- Why?
- Even though you used to be a king,

232
00:07:36,589 --> 00:07:37,789
we can't let you join us easily.

233
00:07:38,189 --> 00:07:41,299
Bring me over what you prepared immediately.

234
00:07:42,429 --> 00:07:43,868
- To whom...
- What are you doing, executioner?

235
00:07:43,869 --> 00:07:44,869
- What?
- "Executioner?"

236
00:07:44,870 --> 00:07:47,168
Off with his head!

237
00:07:47,169 --> 00:07:49,738
- Bring it over here immediately!
- "Executioner."

238
00:07:49,739 --> 00:07:51,068
- "Executioner."
- "Executioner."

239
00:07:51,069 --> 00:07:52,478
- I said, immediately!
- They have their own tasks,

240
00:07:52,479 --> 00:07:54,339
- but they're only imitating him.
- "Executioner."

241
00:07:55,479 --> 00:07:56,779
- General.
- What?

242
00:07:57,679 --> 00:07:58,779
Here is our transfer form.

243
00:07:59,279 --> 00:08:00,519
I'm not the one.

244
00:08:00,819 --> 00:08:02,449
Banish him at once!

245
00:08:03,719 --> 00:08:06,418
- You picked the wrong person.
- Bring it over here.

246
00:08:06,419 --> 00:08:07,619
(The King chose the wrong person.)

247
00:08:08,219 --> 00:08:09,529
Kang Ho Dong, you sinner!

248
00:08:10,059 --> 00:08:11,229
- "Kang Ho Dong."
- Yes.

249
00:08:11,489 --> 00:08:13,599
His head won't come off at once.

250
00:08:14,659 --> 00:08:16,569
Execute him with two strikes.

251
00:08:17,199 --> 00:08:18,468
Cut halfway with each strike.

252
00:08:18,469 --> 00:08:19,698
This school is fun.

253
00:08:19,699 --> 00:08:21,868
- It's fun, indeed.
- I'm glad I'm here.

254
00:08:21,869 --> 00:08:23,268
We're going to have a match.

255
00:08:23,269 --> 00:08:25,108
- History against history.
- Right.

256
00:08:25,109 --> 00:08:26,178
- All right.
- The thing they have in common.

257
00:08:26,179 --> 00:08:28,008
The transfer form to Men on a Mission.

258
00:08:28,009 --> 00:08:30,349
Names, Lee Min Woo, Jung Tae Woo, and Seol Min Seok.

259
00:08:31,349 --> 00:08:32,419
Welcome!

260
00:08:32,819 --> 00:08:36,419
First, we'll check out the thing the guests have in common.

261
00:08:36,889 --> 00:08:39,388
What does this mean? "The connection to Danjong."

262
00:08:39,389 --> 00:08:40,758
- That's right.
- Right.

263
00:08:40,759 --> 00:08:43,028
Both Min Woo and Tae Woo played Danjong.

264
00:08:43,029 --> 00:08:44,989
Do you remember how old you were when you played Danjong?

265
00:08:45,799 --> 00:08:49,328
I don't remember the exact age.

266
00:08:49,329 --> 00:08:51,768
But I played the role in the MBC drama...

267
00:08:51,769 --> 00:08:52,938
"500 Years of Joseon Dynasty, Deep-Rooted Tree."

268
00:08:52,939 --> 00:08:55,268
I played the oldest son of the crown prince.

269
00:08:55,269 --> 00:08:57,308
I played Danjong before he took the throne.

270
00:08:57,309 --> 00:08:59,278
- When he was a little boy?
- Yes.

271
00:08:59,279 --> 00:09:00,378
- What about you, Tae Woo?
- How old were you?

272
00:09:00,379 --> 00:09:01,608
- How old were you?
- As for me...

273
00:09:01,609 --> 00:09:04,378
I played the role in "Han Myong Hoe" at the age of 12.

274
00:09:04,379 --> 00:09:06,048
- Do you still remember that?
- Lee Duk Hwa played in it.

275
00:09:06,049 --> 00:09:07,778
- That's correct.
- He played Han Myong Hoe.

276
00:09:07,779 --> 00:09:10,349
That was my first time playing Danjong.

277
00:09:10,849 --> 00:09:12,519
After that,

278
00:09:12,719 --> 00:09:13,788
I played Danjong again...

279
00:09:13,789 --> 00:09:15,828
- in "The King and the Queen..."
- "The King and the Queen."

280
00:09:15,829 --> 00:09:17,828
- That's right.
- at the age of 17.

281
00:09:17,829 --> 00:09:19,658
It's ironic that Danjong...

282
00:09:19,659 --> 00:09:21,598
ascended the throne at the age of 12...

283
00:09:21,599 --> 00:09:23,628
and met his end at the age of 17.

284
00:09:23,629 --> 00:09:25,938
- That's right.
- And I played Danjong twice,

285
00:09:25,939 --> 00:09:27,768
once at the age of 12 and again at the age of 17.

286
00:09:27,769 --> 00:09:29,038
Why did you spoil it?

287
00:09:29,039 --> 00:09:30,269
I haven't watched the movie yet.

288
00:09:30,869 --> 00:09:32,308
- Darn.
- Hey.

289
00:09:32,309 --> 00:09:34,038
- Gosh. It's your fault!
- He spoiled it.

290
00:09:34,039 --> 00:09:35,608
I was going to watch the movie later today.

291
00:09:35,609 --> 00:09:37,508
- Hey, it's not a spoiler.
- Gosh, seriously.

292
00:09:37,509 --> 00:09:39,778
- It's a historical fact.
- Everyone knows that.

293
00:09:39,779 --> 00:09:41,448
- But I heard it was twice as fun...
- The historical fact he knows...

294
00:09:41,449 --> 00:09:43,388
- if you didn't know that.
- That's true.

295
00:09:43,389 --> 00:09:44,389
I heard it was way more fun.

296
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:46,788
- But this is so...
- Right. That's why I know nothing.

297
00:09:46,789 --> 00:09:47,988
- You can tell historical facts.
- Darn it.

298
00:09:47,989 --> 00:09:50,028
Mr. Seol, do you think it's a spoiler?

299
00:09:50,029 --> 00:09:51,628
- Or not?
- It's a huge spoiler...

300
00:09:51,629 --> 00:09:53,128
for someone like me.

301
00:09:53,129 --> 00:09:56,698
But his age is completely irrelevant to the movie.

302
00:09:56,699 --> 00:09:57,868
Would it still be fun even while knowing this?

303
00:09:57,869 --> 00:10:01,068
We're going to talk about Danjong today.

304
00:10:01,069 --> 00:10:03,838
If those who watched the movie learn about it,

305
00:10:03,839 --> 00:10:05,268
- it becomes ten times more fun.
- I see.

306
00:10:05,269 --> 00:10:07,608
If those who haven't watched it watch it after learning about it,

307
00:10:07,609 --> 00:10:09,308
- they'll be moved 100 times more.
- You see...

308
00:10:09,309 --> 00:10:11,748
"The King's Warden..."

309
00:10:11,749 --> 00:10:13,948
is the talk of the town everywhere.

310
00:10:13,949 --> 00:10:15,278
It's a hot topic everywhere.

311
00:10:15,279 --> 00:10:18,288
But you guys... I mean, you and I are work colleagues.

312
00:10:18,289 --> 00:10:19,558
- That's right.
- Right?

313
00:10:19,559 --> 00:10:21,289
But Ji Hoon is like family to me.

314
00:10:21,419 --> 00:10:22,528
- What?
- What?

315
00:10:22,529 --> 00:10:24,459
- Park Ji Hoon is...
- Why is he like family to you?

316
00:10:24,989 --> 00:10:27,499
(Ho Dong met him on "Dining Together.")

317
00:10:28,059 --> 00:10:31,999
(Ho Dong got so excited just to see Ji Hoon's face.)

318
00:10:32,699 --> 00:10:36,969
(They ate grapes with their arms locked, like a couple.)

319
00:10:37,639 --> 00:10:43,109
(They shared a meal at the same table.)

320
00:10:43,679 --> 00:10:48,949
(They also shared tears.)

321
00:10:49,149 --> 00:10:50,748
Here's what I'm curious about.

322
00:10:50,749 --> 00:10:52,419
They played Danjong before Ji Hoon did.

323
00:10:52,619 --> 00:10:55,088
So Min Woo and Tae Woo, from your perspectives,

324
00:10:55,089 --> 00:10:58,289
how would you evaluate the performance of Ji Hoon...

325
00:10:58,589 --> 00:10:59,798
as Danjong?

326
00:10:59,799 --> 00:11:02,368
Even back when I saw him in "Weak Hero,"

327
00:11:02,369 --> 00:11:04,728
- I thought he had a unique gaze.
- That drama was so good.

328
00:11:04,729 --> 00:11:05,968
- He's extraordinary.
- Right.

329
00:11:05,969 --> 00:11:08,169
His gaze holds a unique blend of sadness,

330
00:11:08,369 --> 00:11:09,838
warmth,

331
00:11:09,839 --> 00:11:12,608
and incredible charisma...

332
00:11:12,609 --> 00:11:14,409
- Yes, that's right.
- all at once.

333
00:11:14,579 --> 00:11:16,948
- He resembles me, right?
- When I ate with him on the show,

334
00:11:16,949 --> 00:11:19,648
- I saw that gaze of Ji Hoon's.
- My gosh.

335
00:11:19,649 --> 00:11:21,578
- I'm tired of it.
- Exactly. I'm sick of it.

336
00:11:21,579 --> 00:11:23,218
- They're laughing because of you.
- He's still...

337
00:11:23,219 --> 00:11:24,849
talking about "Dining Together."

338
00:11:25,119 --> 00:11:27,388
- I saw that unique gaze of his.
- He has a unique gaze.

339
00:11:27,389 --> 00:11:28,459
He has soulful eyes.

340
00:11:28,659 --> 00:11:30,228
- Have you all watched the movie?
- I think you got the wrong idea.

341
00:11:30,229 --> 00:11:32,059
- Of course, I watched it.
- He's at his best today.

342
00:11:32,499 --> 00:11:34,929
When I played Danjong for the 1st time at the age of 12,

343
00:11:35,059 --> 00:11:39,099
I portrayed him as the king who was victimized without understanding...

344
00:11:39,269 --> 00:11:41,239
- the political situation.
- That's right.

345
00:11:41,439 --> 00:11:44,569
But the Danjong portrayed by Ji Hoon in the movie...

346
00:11:44,969 --> 00:11:48,239
shows the dignity of royal blood without him even realizing it.

347
00:11:48,539 --> 00:11:50,849
So rather than remaining silent,

348
00:11:51,109 --> 00:11:52,519
he wants to speak up.

349
00:11:53,349 --> 00:11:56,749
He wants to take action for the sake of the country.

350
00:11:56,889 --> 00:11:59,859
That side of Danjong was well-depicted in the movie.

351
00:12:00,119 --> 00:12:02,889
Also, the blood-thick friendship between the two lead characters...

352
00:12:03,329 --> 00:12:06,028
was portrayed brilliantly. I really enjoyed the movie.

353
00:12:06,029 --> 00:12:07,899
Here's the thing about Ji Hoon that amazed me.

354
00:12:08,099 --> 00:12:11,729
It takes more than three months to shoot a movie.

355
00:12:12,169 --> 00:12:14,399
And there are the beginning and the end of the shoot.

356
00:12:14,539 --> 00:12:17,008
An actor must maintain...

357
00:12:17,009 --> 00:12:19,438
both his physical and emotional state from beginning to end.

358
00:12:19,439 --> 00:12:22,449
And that's not easy to do.

359
00:12:22,749 --> 00:12:26,378
According to an interview, Ji Hoon went to great lengths...

360
00:12:26,379 --> 00:12:29,148
to portray every detail of Danjong's character.

361
00:12:29,149 --> 00:12:31,489
- He's incredible.
- That made me realize...

362
00:12:31,949 --> 00:12:33,218
how amazing he was.

363
00:12:33,219 --> 00:12:35,689
I want to talk about a few scenes to give you some examples,

364
00:12:35,859 --> 00:12:37,688
- but I can't, as it'd be a spoiler.
- Right. You shouldn't.

365
00:12:37,689 --> 00:12:39,498
I do know that Park Ji Hoon played Danjong, though.

366
00:12:39,499 --> 00:12:42,798
Min Seok, Danjong's story has been brought to light again,

367
00:12:42,799 --> 00:12:45,529
nearly 500 years after his passing.

368
00:12:45,769 --> 00:12:48,638
How do you think Sejo would feel about this phenomenon?

369
00:12:48,639 --> 00:12:50,469
- From up above?
- Yes, that's right.

370
00:12:50,869 --> 00:12:53,039
(Sejo usurped the throne from Danjong. How would he feel?)

371
00:12:54,039 --> 00:12:56,209
I'm not sure whether he's up above or down below.

372
00:12:57,709 --> 00:13:01,248
- I'd say he must be wretched.
- Oh, I see.

373
00:13:01,249 --> 00:13:05,089
There's a saying that goes, "You can't hide the sun with a finger."

374
00:13:06,059 --> 00:13:08,219
No matter how hard he tried...

375
00:13:08,889 --> 00:13:11,259
to offer reasons or lies,

376
00:13:11,659 --> 00:13:14,759
history always unveils the truth eventually.

377
00:13:15,259 --> 00:13:18,668
We'll discuss this again later, but Prince Suyang's two sons...

378
00:13:18,669 --> 00:13:20,869
I mean, your karma falls on your descendants.

379
00:13:21,539 --> 00:13:24,268
His two sons died young.

380
00:13:24,269 --> 00:13:26,439
(Crown Prince Uigyeong, his oldest son, died at the age of 20.)

381
00:13:26,539 --> 00:13:30,949
(Yejong, his second son, died at 21, 14 months after his enthronement.)

382
00:13:31,209 --> 00:13:34,148
As for Han Myong Hoe, Prince Yeonsan dug up his corpse and beheaded it...

383
00:13:34,149 --> 00:13:35,479
after his death.

384
00:13:35,889 --> 00:13:39,618
So watching Danjong's story become the talk of the town,

385
00:13:39,619 --> 00:13:42,089
I realized our lives were history themselves,

386
00:13:43,229 --> 00:13:45,859
and so we must live a life we wouldn't be ashamed of.

387
00:13:46,559 --> 00:13:49,328
With the "The King's Warden" craze in full swing,

388
00:13:49,329 --> 00:13:52,129
many clips of the two actors here who played Danjong...

389
00:13:52,599 --> 00:13:54,868
- are on YouTube.
- That's right.

390
00:13:54,869 --> 00:13:57,069
Tae Woo's clip is especially popular.

391
00:13:57,409 --> 00:13:59,108
It's the scene where Danjong and Queen Jeongsun...

392
00:13:59,109 --> 00:14:01,909
wail after hearing they will be exiled to separate locations.

393
00:14:02,509 --> 00:14:05,078
- Do you remember that, Tae Woo?
- Yes, I remember that.

394
00:14:05,079 --> 00:14:07,378
- Do you still remember that?
- We have the footage.

395
00:14:07,379 --> 00:14:08,379
(Tae Woo starred in "Han Myong Hoe" as a little boy 32 years ago.)

396
00:14:09,049 --> 00:14:11,018
(What about the Queen? Will she come with me?)

397
00:14:11,019 --> 00:14:12,558
- Look at Tae Woo.
- Will she come with me?

398
00:14:12,559 --> 00:14:13,718
He's just a little boy.

399
00:14:13,719 --> 00:14:14,719
(Queen Jeongsun played by Park Lucia)

400
00:14:16,229 --> 00:14:21,059
(Her Majesty cannot be with you, Your Majesty.)

401
00:14:21,359 --> 00:14:24,469
(How dare they try to break the husband-wife ties?)

402
00:14:24,929 --> 00:14:26,838
- Doesn't she act anymore?
- Your Majesty, please take me...

403
00:14:26,839 --> 00:14:29,368
where you are going.

404
00:14:29,369 --> 00:14:33,878
(Thank you, my lady.)

405
00:14:33,879 --> 00:14:38,479
(I shall never forget your sincerity.)

406
00:14:39,079 --> 00:14:44,019
(Your Majesty, please do not cast me aside.)

407
00:14:45,789 --> 00:14:50,428
(I am a mere prince now.)

408
00:14:50,429 --> 00:14:53,129
(How could I defy the King's command?)

409
00:14:53,299 --> 00:14:56,528
(The two child actors performed incredibly well.)

410
00:14:56,529 --> 00:14:57,629
He was a great actor back then too.

411
00:14:58,169 --> 00:15:01,398
Is the child actress who performed with you...

412
00:15:01,399 --> 00:15:02,908
no longer acting?

413
00:15:02,909 --> 00:15:05,878
- I guess she quit a long time ago.
- She's incredible...

414
00:15:05,879 --> 00:15:08,378
- She's like an acting prodigy.
- I was just getting into it,

415
00:15:08,379 --> 00:15:10,448
but then he ruined the mood by asking if she was still acting.

416
00:15:10,449 --> 00:15:11,879
Since their voices overlapped,

417
00:15:11,979 --> 00:15:13,078
I just could not...

418
00:15:13,079 --> 00:15:15,548
- Is she no longer acting?
- fully immerse myself.

419
00:15:15,549 --> 00:15:17,788
(Jang Hoon's voice kept disturbing Ho Dong.)

420
00:15:17,789 --> 00:15:19,858
Whenever I was about to tear up, he asked,

421
00:15:19,859 --> 00:15:22,628
- "Is she no longer acting?"
- Exactly.

422
00:15:22,629 --> 00:15:24,658
Watch it again on a streaming platform.

423
00:15:24,659 --> 00:15:26,128
That's a scene...

424
00:15:26,129 --> 00:15:27,598
- from the drama "Han Myong Hoe."
- Yes.

425
00:15:27,599 --> 00:15:29,298
- Right. I watched it...
- Just say it.

426
00:15:29,299 --> 00:15:32,228
- Lee Duk Hwa played Han Myong Hoe.
- I watched it when it aired.

427
00:15:32,229 --> 00:15:35,038
- I was 12 at the time.
- Right.

428
00:15:35,039 --> 00:15:37,569
I played Danjong in the drama "Han Myong Hoe."

429
00:15:37,769 --> 00:15:40,209
I did a great job and won the Best Child Actor Award.

430
00:15:40,809 --> 00:15:43,709
And many years later, I was offered to play Danjong again.

431
00:15:43,979 --> 00:15:45,949
I ran away to avoid taking it.

432
00:15:46,079 --> 00:15:49,448
I didn't want to play the same role or play in a similar drama.

433
00:15:49,449 --> 00:15:51,388
Also, it was not easy for me to portray Danjong...

434
00:15:51,389 --> 00:15:54,059
from his childhood all the way to his death.

435
00:15:54,189 --> 00:15:55,888
There were so many emotional scenes...

436
00:15:55,889 --> 00:15:58,088
- that it drained my energy.
- Right. Of course.

437
00:15:58,089 --> 00:15:59,659
So I kept turning the offer down.

438
00:16:00,099 --> 00:16:02,199
While no one got cast for the role of Danjong,

439
00:16:02,399 --> 00:16:04,329
an actress got the role of Queen Jeongsun.

440
00:16:04,829 --> 00:16:06,968
- And it was Kim Min Jung.
- Oh, my.

441
00:16:06,969 --> 00:16:07,969
(Kim Min Jung played Queen Jeongsun in "The King and the Queen.")

442
00:16:08,139 --> 00:16:09,808
- She was so pretty back then.
- Right.

443
00:16:09,809 --> 00:16:13,279
- So I just took the role.
- Just to see her?

444
00:16:14,909 --> 00:16:16,009
Hold on. Tae Woo.

445
00:16:16,249 --> 00:16:19,518
Queen Jeongsun is one year older than Danjong.

446
00:16:19,519 --> 00:16:20,648
- That's correct.
- Yes.

447
00:16:20,649 --> 00:16:21,748
- So...
- I'm surprised he knows that.

448
00:16:21,749 --> 00:16:22,988
What's the age gap between you and Min Jung?

449
00:16:22,989 --> 00:16:24,218
She and I are very close friends of the same age.

450
00:16:24,219 --> 00:16:26,188
- As a child actor, - You two are the same age?

451
00:16:26,189 --> 00:16:29,088
I worked with Min Jung so often, doing fashion shoots, commercials,

452
00:16:29,089 --> 00:16:30,858
and dramas.

453
00:16:30,859 --> 00:16:33,528
By the way, why were Danjong and Queen Jeongsun separated?

454
00:16:33,529 --> 00:16:35,459
Couldn't they be sent to the same location?

455
00:16:35,629 --> 00:16:37,299
- I'm curious about that too.
- Right.

456
00:16:37,399 --> 00:16:40,198
Not long ago, a professor I respect appeared on a TV show...

457
00:16:40,199 --> 00:16:41,539
and talked about the story.

458
00:16:41,899 --> 00:16:43,709
And here's his theory on the matter.

459
00:16:44,169 --> 00:16:45,439
If they were sent to the same location,

460
00:16:45,639 --> 00:16:47,809
- and if they had a son, - If they have a child...

461
00:16:47,979 --> 00:16:49,179
- That's right.
- that'd be a headache.

462
00:16:49,349 --> 00:16:50,549
I agree with his theory.

463
00:16:50,709 --> 00:16:52,748
You see, Queen Jeongsun, whom he's talking about,

464
00:16:52,749 --> 00:16:54,078
lived a long life,

465
00:16:54,079 --> 00:16:55,448
- reaching well over 80.
- Really?

466
00:16:55,449 --> 00:16:57,248
- At that time?
- Did she live a long life?

467
00:16:57,249 --> 00:16:58,289
That's a really long life for that time.

468
00:16:58,419 --> 00:17:00,919
I knew that Jang Hoon was interested in history...

469
00:17:01,189 --> 00:17:03,359
- and studied a lot.
- Seol Min Seok.

470
00:17:03,629 --> 00:17:05,458
- But I rediscovered Ho Dong today.
- No, that's...

471
00:17:05,459 --> 00:17:08,158
- I don't know that much.
- He crammed for today.

472
00:17:08,159 --> 00:17:09,699
Ask him for details. He'll get everything wrong.

473
00:17:10,799 --> 00:17:12,939
He's just talking about what he memorized.

474
00:17:13,169 --> 00:17:14,498
- Ask him for details.
- Come on. I mean...

475
00:17:14,499 --> 00:17:17,368
- Before we started the shoot, - I had some basic knowledge of it.

476
00:17:17,369 --> 00:17:20,178
- we received a summary.
- How would he know the details?

477
00:17:20,179 --> 00:17:23,249
- Queen Jeongsun lived to 80?
- She and Danjong were separated.

478
00:17:23,579 --> 00:17:25,309
Following the tragedy of Danjong,

479
00:17:25,679 --> 00:17:27,148
she was demoted to a government slave.

480
00:17:27,149 --> 00:17:29,149
To be exact, a female government slave.

481
00:17:29,589 --> 00:17:30,819
She was demoted to a female government slave.

482
00:17:31,019 --> 00:17:35,259
Sejo made her live with female Buddhist monks.

483
00:17:35,489 --> 00:17:37,958
- She dyed fabric...
- Right.

484
00:17:37,959 --> 00:17:39,429
to earn a living.

485
00:17:39,899 --> 00:17:42,198
One story goes that whenever she put fabric into water,

486
00:17:42,199 --> 00:17:43,469
it turned reddish purple.

487
00:17:44,099 --> 00:17:45,969
That means she had so much resentment inside.

488
00:17:46,499 --> 00:17:50,039
Yet, she lived her tragic life until she reached 82.

489
00:17:50,409 --> 00:17:51,809
She passed away at the age of 82.

490
00:17:52,039 --> 00:17:53,509
She lived a painful life, right?

491
00:17:53,839 --> 00:17:55,239
But if you look back on history,

492
00:17:55,639 --> 00:17:58,779
she lived until she was 82, carrying all that resentment in her heart.

493
00:17:59,179 --> 00:18:01,879
She saw Sejo's sons die one after another.

494
00:18:02,079 --> 00:18:04,949
She witnessed Sejo's painful death due to his skin disease.

495
00:18:05,119 --> 00:18:07,418
And she also witnessed Han Myong Hoe's corpse...

496
00:18:07,419 --> 00:18:09,488
being exhumed and beheaded by the command of Prince Yeonsan.

497
00:18:09,489 --> 00:18:11,128
(She even witnessed Han Myong Hoe's corpse being exhumed and beheaded.)

498
00:18:11,129 --> 00:18:12,259
So I assume...

499
00:18:13,159 --> 00:18:15,359
that it helped her...

500
00:18:15,899 --> 00:18:19,898
ease her resentment to some extent.

501
00:18:19,899 --> 00:18:20,938
Exactly. Her resentment...

502
00:18:20,939 --> 00:18:22,668
Min Woo played both Danjong...

503
00:18:22,669 --> 00:18:24,838
- and Danjong's brother-in-law.
- That's correct.

504
00:18:24,839 --> 00:18:27,079
His performances were incredible.

505
00:18:27,539 --> 00:18:28,608
- He played his brother-in-law too?
- In the KBS drama...

506
00:18:28,609 --> 00:18:29,709
"The Princess's Man,"

507
00:18:29,909 --> 00:18:31,308
I played the husband of Princess Gyeonghye...

508
00:18:31,309 --> 00:18:32,749
who was Danjong's older sister.

509
00:18:33,049 --> 00:18:35,249
- I played Jeong Jong.
- Jeong Jong.

510
00:18:35,519 --> 00:18:37,588
Since he was Princess Gyeonghye's husband,

511
00:18:37,589 --> 00:18:39,459
he made a lot of effort to support Danjong's reinstatement.

512
00:18:39,484 --> 00:18:41,124
He joined forces with Prince Geumseong...

513
00:18:41,519 --> 00:18:44,559
and defied Sejo's authority.

514
00:18:44,629 --> 00:18:45,828
In the end, he was executed...

515
00:18:45,829 --> 00:18:48,228
- by drawing and quartering.
- "Drawing and quartering?"

516
00:18:48,229 --> 00:18:49,861
- "Drawing and quartering?"
- Drawing and quartering.

517
00:18:50,299 --> 00:18:51,668
Oh, dismemberment execution?

518
00:18:51,669 --> 00:18:53,338
- In the drama...
- Dismemberment?

519
00:18:53,339 --> 00:18:54,838
- There's a scene... There it is.
- Prince Suyang.

520
00:18:54,839 --> 00:18:55,899
It's also called "Lingchi."

521
00:18:56,309 --> 00:18:57,868
- Oh, he played Gung Ye.
- Listen to me very carefully.

522
00:18:57,869 --> 00:18:59,139
(Listen to me very carefully.)

523
00:18:59,409 --> 00:19:02,209
(Jeong Jong, Princess Gyeonghye's husband)

524
00:19:03,049 --> 00:19:04,049
(My soul shall remain...)

525
00:19:04,049 --> 00:19:05,049
(Princess Gyeonghye played by Hong Soo Hyun)

526
00:19:05,709 --> 00:19:08,248
(to haunt you, )

527
00:19:08,249 --> 00:19:10,019
(even in your dreams.)

528
00:19:11,619 --> 00:19:12,918
Hong Soo Hyun played Princess Gyeonghye?

529
00:19:12,919 --> 00:19:14,219
(Make sure nothing but screams escape his lips.)

530
00:19:21,159 --> 00:19:22,229
That's how the execution is performed.

531
00:19:24,869 --> 00:19:28,939
(Jeong Jong met a tragic end, being drawn and quartered.)

532
00:19:31,209 --> 00:19:32,269
That was realistic.

533
00:19:32,509 --> 00:19:35,578
First of all, many people are mistaken.

534
00:19:35,579 --> 00:19:38,279
They get confused drawing and quartering with Lingchi.

535
00:19:38,749 --> 00:19:41,518
People usually picture limbs being torn apart when they hear "Lingchi."

536
00:19:41,519 --> 00:19:44,289
- "Lingchi."
- Lingchi is a different process.

537
00:19:44,449 --> 00:19:45,889
- Different how?
- They slice away the flesh.

538
00:19:46,219 --> 00:19:48,319
- Oh, goodness.
- Gosh. Seriously.

539
00:19:48,589 --> 00:19:50,988
They slice away the flesh bit by bit, and at the end,

540
00:19:50,989 --> 00:19:54,028
- they cut the limbs off.
- That's so cruel.

541
00:19:54,029 --> 00:19:56,529
- What crimes lead to Lingchi?
- They slice away the flesh?

542
00:19:56,799 --> 00:19:59,939
The crimes that lead to Lingchi include treason...

543
00:20:00,469 --> 00:20:03,209
and immoral crimes that undermine the social hierarchy.

544
00:20:03,439 --> 00:20:04,708
- Such felonies...
- My gosh. That's scary.

545
00:20:04,709 --> 00:20:05,739
were punishable by Lingchi.

546
00:20:06,139 --> 00:20:07,879
- But here's the problem.
- It's basically dissection...

547
00:20:08,139 --> 00:20:09,278
- Many Asian countries...
- while the person is still alive.

548
00:20:09,279 --> 00:20:10,408
- believed in Confucianism.
- Yes.

549
00:20:10,409 --> 00:20:11,578
Confucianism teaches that you must not damage your body,

550
00:20:11,579 --> 00:20:12,748
- as it is a gift from your parents.
- Yes.

551
00:20:12,749 --> 00:20:14,378
- They didn't even trim their beard.
- That's right.

552
00:20:14,379 --> 00:20:17,418
So it was something that Asians feared most.

553
00:20:17,419 --> 00:20:18,919
- Dying with a damaged body.
- That makes sense.

554
00:20:19,119 --> 00:20:20,619
That's why they were grateful for death by poison.

555
00:20:21,019 --> 00:20:22,088
They thought it was better?

556
00:20:22,089 --> 00:20:23,288
(They were grateful for death by poison?)

557
00:20:23,289 --> 00:20:25,858
They thanked the king even though they'd die painfully.

558
00:20:25,859 --> 00:20:28,098
Because the king allowed them to die without their bodies being damaged.

559
00:20:28,099 --> 00:20:29,598
Oh, that's why they always express their gratitude in dramas...

560
00:20:29,599 --> 00:20:32,099
- when they're executed by poison.
- They were actually grateful.

561
00:20:32,269 --> 00:20:34,498
- That's why they thank the king.
- That's right.

562
00:20:34,499 --> 00:20:36,739
But it's different in the West.

563
00:20:37,269 --> 00:20:40,108
In Europe, they were grateful for painless death.

564
00:20:40,109 --> 00:20:41,178
- Was it considered neat?
- Go on.

565
00:20:41,179 --> 00:20:44,078
So, members of the nobility were executed by beheading.

566
00:20:44,079 --> 00:20:47,479
- Just like Marie Antoinette.
- We'll get to that in a bit.

567
00:20:48,049 --> 00:20:50,788
Commoners were often executed by drawing and quartering.

568
00:20:50,789 --> 00:20:52,889
Or they were burned at the stake.

569
00:20:53,859 --> 00:20:55,088
What made them harsh was pain.

570
00:20:55,089 --> 00:20:56,629
Bodily damage was disregarded.

571
00:20:56,659 --> 00:20:58,789
After the French Revolution,

572
00:20:59,059 --> 00:21:01,399
even punishments shifted toward democracy.

573
00:21:01,659 --> 00:21:03,128
Commoners should also be killed painlessly.

574
00:21:03,129 --> 00:21:04,228
With that, the guillotine was made.

575
00:21:04,229 --> 00:21:05,928
- The result was that?
- The two are different.

576
00:21:05,929 --> 00:21:07,098
Beheaded at once, right?

577
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:08,938
Lingchi isn't something to be said...

578
00:21:08,939 --> 00:21:10,508
- so lightly.
- How scary.

579
00:21:10,509 --> 00:21:13,078
- I didn't know much about...
- Yes?

580
00:21:13,079 --> 00:21:15,209
Jeong Jong and Princess Gyeonghye.

581
00:21:15,479 --> 00:21:17,479
You played Jeong Jong, right?

582
00:21:17,579 --> 00:21:18,808
- Yes, Jeong Jong.
- Correct.

583
00:21:18,809 --> 00:21:20,779
Not King Jeongjong of Joseon,

584
00:21:20,949 --> 00:21:22,248
but a man named Jeong Jong.

585
00:21:22,249 --> 00:21:24,889
Danjong and his older sister were full siblings.

586
00:21:25,089 --> 00:21:27,159
The two were very close.

587
00:21:27,319 --> 00:21:29,688
Even when Prince Suyang launched the Gyeyu Coup,

588
00:21:29,689 --> 00:21:30,859
he was at his older sister's place.

589
00:21:31,029 --> 00:21:33,929
The older sister's husband was played by Min Woo.

590
00:21:34,899 --> 00:21:37,669
Jeong Jong was able to marry Princess Gyeonghye...

591
00:21:37,929 --> 00:21:40,069
because he was a noble from a fallen family.

592
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:44,208
"Have them marry, and there won't be any future troubles."

593
00:21:44,209 --> 00:21:47,208
Sejo secretly chose Jeong Jong as the groom...

594
00:21:47,209 --> 00:21:48,708
and made the two marry.

595
00:21:48,709 --> 00:21:50,608
But that very Jeong Jong...

596
00:21:50,609 --> 00:21:52,508
went around meeting people, like Prince Geumseong,

597
00:21:52,509 --> 00:21:56,518
to conspire, which led him to his death.

598
00:21:56,519 --> 00:21:57,549
That was the overall story.

599
00:21:57,989 --> 00:21:59,889
The woman who was crying earlier...

600
00:21:59,989 --> 00:22:01,958
Hong Soo Hyun played Princess Gyeonghye.

601
00:22:01,959 --> 00:22:03,688
- Right.
- The close older sister.

602
00:22:03,689 --> 00:22:05,388
- Jeong Jong...
- Knowing the history...

603
00:22:05,389 --> 00:22:07,058
makes it more relatable.

604
00:22:07,059 --> 00:22:08,358
The more you know, the more you see.

605
00:22:08,359 --> 00:22:10,469
At first, I thought, "Why is that woman crying?"

606
00:22:10,769 --> 00:22:12,699
Hong Soo Hyun kept crying, you know?

607
00:22:12,869 --> 00:22:15,839
The actors and actresses must feel a great sense of responsibility.

608
00:22:16,309 --> 00:22:19,438
When you're in a historical or period drama,

609
00:22:19,439 --> 00:22:21,908
you feel a lot of pressure.

610
00:22:21,909 --> 00:22:24,479
It's because you have to act out a real figure...

611
00:22:24,549 --> 00:22:26,919
in an era that actually existed,

612
00:22:27,049 --> 00:22:28,479
so the pressure....

613
00:22:29,279 --> 00:22:31,348
is greater than that of a normal creative work.

614
00:22:31,349 --> 00:22:33,258
You must know the background information.

615
00:22:33,259 --> 00:22:35,288
- You can't cut corners.
- It's important.

616
00:22:35,289 --> 00:22:38,258
To some viewers, the actor or actress...

617
00:22:38,259 --> 00:22:40,228
leaves a lasting impression...

618
00:22:40,229 --> 00:22:42,199
- of the role.
- Exactly.

619
00:22:42,359 --> 00:22:43,869
In Min Woo's case...

620
00:22:44,369 --> 00:22:45,869
- In "Tears of the Dragon,"
- I remember.

621
00:22:46,169 --> 00:22:48,398
Min Woo pulled off the role...

622
00:22:48,399 --> 00:22:51,109
of Prince Yangnyeong so well.

623
00:22:51,369 --> 00:22:54,739
So when I see or mention...

624
00:22:55,139 --> 00:22:58,249
the term "Prince Yangnyeong,"

625
00:22:58,809 --> 00:23:01,279
Min Woo's face is the first to pop up in my head.

626
00:23:01,919 --> 00:23:03,748
It was Min Woo's best work yet.

627
00:23:03,749 --> 00:23:05,088
Back in "Tears of the Dragon,"

628
00:23:05,089 --> 00:23:06,419
I was actually Prince Chungnyeong.

629
00:23:07,489 --> 00:23:08,558
I was first cast to be...

630
00:23:08,559 --> 00:23:10,028
- Prince Chungnyeong.
- At first?

631
00:23:10,029 --> 00:23:13,099
I read about 40 historical and history-related...

632
00:23:13,599 --> 00:23:15,359
- You read them all?
- books.

633
00:23:15,459 --> 00:23:17,029
I wrote up...

634
00:23:18,129 --> 00:23:19,899
a so-called report...

635
00:23:20,039 --> 00:23:22,369
for Producer Kim Jae Hyeong.

636
00:23:22,439 --> 00:23:24,708
When I gave it to him, the producer tossed it back to me...

637
00:23:24,709 --> 00:23:26,238
after skimming it and said,

638
00:23:26,239 --> 00:23:27,239
"You're Prince Yangnyeong."

639
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:28,839
"Go get ready to play Prince Yangnyeong."

640
00:23:28,879 --> 00:23:30,579
My heart dropped at that moment.

641
00:23:30,879 --> 00:23:34,849
Producer Kim said the drama rounds off with Taejo of Joseon,

642
00:23:35,019 --> 00:23:37,219
Yi Bang Won, and Prince Chungnyeong.

643
00:23:37,519 --> 00:23:39,089
That was how I got cast.

644
00:23:39,419 --> 00:23:40,759
But to say I'm suddenly Prince Yangnyeong?

645
00:23:40,919 --> 00:23:42,358
Even so, the shoot started.

646
00:23:42,359 --> 00:23:43,529
(Played Prince Yangnyeong in the end)

647
00:23:43,829 --> 00:23:44,889
But what's this?

648
00:23:45,729 --> 00:23:47,158
The lines were endless.

649
00:23:47,159 --> 00:23:48,698
- Prince Yangnyeong...
- Even better.

650
00:23:48,699 --> 00:23:50,069
- had way more screen time.
- I see.

651
00:23:50,929 --> 00:23:53,169
I still don't know why my role was changed.

652
00:23:53,569 --> 00:23:55,338
Min Woo, I was told...

653
00:23:55,339 --> 00:23:57,138
I'm the 38th-generation descendant of Prince Yangnyeong.

654
00:23:57,139 --> 00:23:58,609
- It must be true, right?
- Really?

655
00:23:58,739 --> 00:23:59,909
I wouldn't know.

656
00:24:01,209 --> 00:24:02,779
Then who should I ask?

657
00:24:02,949 --> 00:24:04,449
- Prince Yangnyeong.
- No, he wouldn't.

658
00:24:04,749 --> 00:24:07,179
Out of all the period dramas Min Woo was in,

659
00:24:07,279 --> 00:24:09,818
"Tears of the Dragon" was the biggest hit.

660
00:24:09,819 --> 00:24:12,349
From what I remember, the ratings went over 56 percent.

661
00:24:12,519 --> 00:24:16,088
But what's a surprise is that you rarely played a king's role.

662
00:24:16,089 --> 00:24:18,389
No. Prince Yeonsan.

663
00:24:18,659 --> 00:24:19,698
Prince Yeonsan.

664
00:24:19,699 --> 00:24:22,458
Gojong of the Korean Empire in "Gunman in Joseon."

665
00:24:22,459 --> 00:24:23,628
(Min Woo played Prince Yeonsan and Gojong of the Korean Empire.)

666
00:24:23,629 --> 00:24:27,569
Two years ago, I played the king of Joseon as a special cast...

667
00:24:27,939 --> 00:24:30,209
in MBC's "The Story of Park's Marriage Contract."

668
00:24:30,239 --> 00:24:32,739
On the contrary, Tae Woo was enthroned several times, right?

669
00:24:33,239 --> 00:24:34,979
Before or after Joseon?

670
00:24:36,139 --> 00:24:38,179
- For Joseon, - For real?

671
00:24:39,149 --> 00:24:41,449
- I played Danjong twice.
- Okay.

672
00:24:41,679 --> 00:24:44,288
In the drama "World of Woman," I played Injong.

673
00:24:44,289 --> 00:24:46,388
- You were in "World of Woman?"
- Yes.

674
00:24:46,389 --> 00:24:47,559
I was too.

675
00:24:48,289 --> 00:24:50,388
- When were you in it?
- Dramas in the past were long,

676
00:24:50,389 --> 00:24:53,299
- Didn't it air for two years?
- so when you appeared differed.

677
00:24:53,659 --> 00:24:55,958
You don't watch the drama once you're done, do you?

678
00:24:55,959 --> 00:24:58,129
He doesn't even watch his own parts.

679
00:25:00,099 --> 00:25:01,869
Min Woo is a total boomer.

680
00:25:02,499 --> 00:25:05,008
- Before Joseon, for Goryeo, - Yes?

681
00:25:05,009 --> 00:25:07,038
I played Huijong in "Age of Warriors."

682
00:25:07,039 --> 00:25:08,479
You were in "Age of Warriors?"

683
00:25:09,179 --> 00:25:10,179
(It's not a replay.)

684
00:25:10,180 --> 00:25:11,548
Were you in it too, Min Woo?

685
00:25:11,549 --> 00:25:15,119
"Age of Warriors" was my last work before joining the army.

686
00:25:15,279 --> 00:25:17,288
Were you two in different studios?

687
00:25:17,289 --> 00:25:19,488
- Were there different studios?
- A month after dying...

688
00:25:19,489 --> 00:25:21,358
in "Age of Warriors," I joined the army.

689
00:25:21,359 --> 00:25:23,459
Now that I think about it,

690
00:25:23,489 --> 00:25:25,988
Min Woo and I were in many dramas together.

691
00:25:25,989 --> 00:25:28,329
But those dramas were lengthy.

692
00:25:28,529 --> 00:25:30,628
- The covered period was wide.
- A long...

693
00:25:30,629 --> 00:25:32,529
- It was a long historical drama.
- Exactly.

694
00:25:32,629 --> 00:25:34,638
- Either way, you die, Min Woo.
- Adults...

695
00:25:34,639 --> 00:25:36,608
- Yes, I usually die.
- Viewers think...

696
00:25:36,609 --> 00:25:38,608
- Min Woo and I are close.
- Right.

697
00:25:38,609 --> 00:25:42,778
But we've never once acted face-to-face together.

698
00:25:42,779 --> 00:25:44,148
You had no chance to meet.

699
00:25:44,149 --> 00:25:45,948
Even if it's the same role,

700
00:25:45,949 --> 00:25:49,178
acting it out as a prince and a king is different?

701
00:25:49,179 --> 00:25:51,649
Once you become a king, it gets easy.

702
00:25:53,789 --> 00:25:55,119
- The shoot...
- You move less.

703
00:25:57,489 --> 00:25:59,158
- Regardless of the weather?
- Yes.

704
00:25:59,159 --> 00:26:01,798
- How much you move is limited.
- The king always stays seated.

705
00:26:01,799 --> 00:26:04,128
- Usually...
- The king's age doesn't matter.

706
00:26:04,129 --> 00:26:05,499
You just stay seated.

707
00:26:05,699 --> 00:26:07,799
Everyone comes in and out of my room.

708
00:26:08,039 --> 00:26:10,569
Even the prince has to visit me.

709
00:26:10,869 --> 00:26:13,109
- The king simply stays seated.
- I'm always sitting down.

710
00:26:13,739 --> 00:26:16,179
- Even when shooting outdoors, - Yes?

711
00:26:16,279 --> 00:26:18,848
there may be endless people...

712
00:26:18,849 --> 00:26:22,079
down on their knees...

713
00:26:22,379 --> 00:26:24,949
- within the palace.
- Right.

714
00:26:25,119 --> 00:26:27,289
All I need to do is open the door and step out.

715
00:26:27,659 --> 00:26:28,858
You're right.

716
00:26:28,859 --> 00:26:30,488
- The end. I'm done.
- Nice.

717
00:26:30,489 --> 00:26:32,228
Meals must be different as well.

718
00:26:32,229 --> 00:26:33,898
Right. When it comes to meals,

719
00:26:33,899 --> 00:26:36,058
- the king has it tough.
- Yes?

720
00:26:36,059 --> 00:26:37,229
- What? Why?
- Why?

721
00:26:37,799 --> 00:26:40,069
It was when the working environment was poor.

722
00:26:40,339 --> 00:26:42,338
- That would be about 40 years ago.
- Right.

723
00:26:42,339 --> 00:26:44,939
- Meals are prepped...
- Do they go bad?

724
00:26:45,269 --> 00:26:46,708
much in advance.

725
00:26:46,709 --> 00:26:49,378
- Of course.
- I guess the food went bad.

726
00:26:49,379 --> 00:26:52,309
- The environment...
- The food was prepped properly,

727
00:26:52,609 --> 00:26:55,748
but the shoot lasted until the afternoon and evening.

728
00:26:55,749 --> 00:26:56,819
- Spoiled.
- They'd go bad.

729
00:26:56,889 --> 00:26:58,889
- Look closely, - Yes?

730
00:26:59,589 --> 00:27:01,489
and the king barely eats.

731
00:27:04,059 --> 00:27:05,358
Because the food has gone bad.

732
00:27:05,359 --> 00:27:07,159
- Kings don't eat the prepped meal?
- No.

733
00:27:07,829 --> 00:27:09,158
- Nobody bothers to eat it.
- Nobody bothers?

734
00:27:09,159 --> 00:27:11,729
Even when the scene doesn't require it,

735
00:27:12,199 --> 00:27:14,539
the king lifts his spoon up...

736
00:27:15,399 --> 00:27:16,468
(Clearing his throat)

737
00:27:16,469 --> 00:27:17,509
(Putting it down)

738
00:27:18,209 --> 00:27:19,909
That's a trick.

739
00:27:20,339 --> 00:27:21,979
- Drink.
- You just have a drink.

740
00:27:22,579 --> 00:27:23,978
But Min Woo...

741
00:27:23,979 --> 00:27:25,779
- The king doesn't eat the snacks.
- I heard...

742
00:27:26,149 --> 00:27:28,419
Here's another pro of being a king.

743
00:27:28,579 --> 00:27:29,918
It's something Jo Jae Yun told me.

744
00:27:29,919 --> 00:27:32,018
"If someone needs to be captured,"

745
00:27:32,019 --> 00:27:34,258
"you only need to say the line in the main hall."

746
00:27:34,259 --> 00:27:35,758
"But I need to travel and shoot..."

747
00:27:35,759 --> 00:27:37,858
"in different locations..."

748
00:27:37,859 --> 00:27:39,558
- "to capture that one person."
- Right.

749
00:27:39,559 --> 00:27:42,228
But be in one scene, you get paid the same.

750
00:27:42,229 --> 00:27:44,998
Be in ten scenes, you still get paid the same.

751
00:27:44,999 --> 00:27:46,198
- Right.
- Make an order...

752
00:27:46,199 --> 00:27:48,098
from the main hall, and I get paid.

753
00:27:48,099 --> 00:27:49,468
- "Go capture him."
- The end.

754
00:27:49,469 --> 00:27:51,209
But eunuchs and generals...

755
00:27:51,269 --> 00:27:53,578
must fight, ride horses,

756
00:27:53,579 --> 00:27:55,378
and shoot for days...

757
00:27:55,379 --> 00:27:57,379
to earn as much.

758
00:27:57,649 --> 00:28:00,349
He mentioned how unfair it was and such.

759
00:28:00,379 --> 00:28:01,678
- But...
- By the way,

760
00:28:01,679 --> 00:28:03,919
you both played Prince Yeonsan.

761
00:28:04,149 --> 00:28:06,819
You killed a ton of people back then, right?

762
00:28:07,159 --> 00:28:11,159
For 3 weeks, I'm sure I killed over 200 people.

763
00:28:11,289 --> 00:28:12,428
Goodness.

764
00:28:12,429 --> 00:28:15,359
Did Prince Yeonsan kill the most out of all the kings in history?

765
00:28:16,129 --> 00:28:17,369
From what I see,

766
00:28:17,529 --> 00:28:21,499
how many people he killed doesn't matter.

767
00:28:22,099 --> 00:28:23,569
The justification is what matters.

768
00:28:24,109 --> 00:28:25,138
Yi Bang Won's father...

769
00:28:25,139 --> 00:28:26,339
- is Taejo, right?
- Yes.

770
00:28:26,739 --> 00:28:29,708
After killing his brothers, Yi Bang Won became the king.

771
00:28:29,709 --> 00:28:31,278
(Taejong became king after removing all threats.)

772
00:28:31,279 --> 00:28:32,309
But here's the thing.

773
00:28:33,419 --> 00:28:36,619
"I'll take full responsibility."

774
00:28:37,419 --> 00:28:38,989
"I'll strengthen the regal power..."

775
00:28:39,149 --> 00:28:42,519
"and bequeath a strong country," was what he had in mind.

776
00:28:42,719 --> 00:28:44,658
Sejong accomplished great achievements,

777
00:28:44,659 --> 00:28:45,929
thanks to Taejong's works.

778
00:28:46,189 --> 00:28:48,359
Taejong made all the sacrifices.

779
00:28:48,699 --> 00:28:51,068
Strengthening the regal power for the country and the people...

780
00:28:51,069 --> 00:28:52,469
was his reason.

781
00:28:52,699 --> 00:28:53,899
So even by killing millions,

782
00:28:54,099 --> 00:28:55,869
the later generations evaluated him optimistically.

783
00:28:55,969 --> 00:28:57,808
But when it came to Prince Yeonsan, he had no sense of altruism.

784
00:28:57,809 --> 00:29:00,908
He killed people out of personal grudges,

785
00:29:00,909 --> 00:29:02,339
ambitions, and joy.

786
00:29:02,679 --> 00:29:04,149
The number doesn't matter.

787
00:29:04,279 --> 00:29:05,279
- You're right.
- It's the justification...

788
00:29:05,280 --> 00:29:06,308
and purpose.

789
00:29:06,309 --> 00:29:07,718
Either way, he did kill a lot.

790
00:29:07,719 --> 00:29:10,048
- Say that our members...
- Yes?

791
00:29:10,049 --> 00:29:13,618
were in a period drama. Who would we play?

792
00:29:13,619 --> 00:29:16,288
Isn't it obvious who Kang Ho Dong and I will play?

793
00:29:16,289 --> 00:29:18,759
- Im Kkeok Jeong?
- A barbarian or something.

794
00:29:19,159 --> 00:29:22,128
I'm Emperor of Liao.

795
00:29:22,129 --> 00:29:24,128
- No kings?
- Do we have no kings among us?

796
00:29:24,129 --> 00:29:25,199
You do.

797
00:29:25,299 --> 00:29:26,428
I think it's Soo Geun.

798
00:29:26,429 --> 00:29:27,739
- As a king?
- What?

799
00:29:28,239 --> 00:29:29,499
Have him come in at once.

800
00:29:29,839 --> 00:29:31,238
- Who?
- Who?

801
00:29:31,239 --> 00:29:33,778
But the royal robe would be too long on him.

802
00:29:33,779 --> 00:29:34,838
It needs to be tailored.

803
00:29:34,839 --> 00:29:36,408
- In the past...
- He'll drag it around.

804
00:29:36,409 --> 00:29:38,708
Were kings in the past tall?

805
00:29:38,709 --> 00:29:41,748
Please explain why you think Soo Geun is fit to play a king.

806
00:29:41,749 --> 00:29:43,649
- What a surprise.
- First off,

807
00:29:44,089 --> 00:29:45,618
- Soo Geun has...
- I was shocked.

808
00:29:45,619 --> 00:29:49,789
a face that can pull off a lowborn to a royal family member.

809
00:29:49,959 --> 00:29:51,088
(A versatile actor in period drama)

810
00:29:51,089 --> 00:29:54,499
Look at him, and he'd be perfect for a lowborn's role.

811
00:29:54,759 --> 00:29:58,068
He'd do well even as a merchant.

812
00:29:58,069 --> 00:29:59,529
Welcome.

813
00:30:00,299 --> 00:30:02,698
- A king.
- But what I like the most is...

814
00:30:02,699 --> 00:30:04,808
how his face has both good and bad.

815
00:30:04,809 --> 00:30:06,369
(Good and bad coexist in his face.)

816
00:30:07,079 --> 00:30:08,438
Ho Dong doesn't look happy.

817
00:30:08,439 --> 00:30:10,679
Lock him up in the pigpen!

818
00:30:11,479 --> 00:30:14,619
Keep feeding him until it's hard to tell...

819
00:30:14,879 --> 00:30:16,919
whether he's a human or a pig.

820
00:30:17,589 --> 00:30:20,089
I beg your kindness, Your Majesty.

821
00:30:20,759 --> 00:30:21,959
He's intimidating.

822
00:30:22,389 --> 00:30:23,828
(Scared)

823
00:30:23,829 --> 00:30:25,229
Please.

824
00:30:25,389 --> 00:30:26,998
A lowborn...

825
00:30:26,999 --> 00:30:28,599
I'm not feeling well,

826
00:30:28,899 --> 00:30:30,529
but to live with pigs?

827
00:30:30,669 --> 00:30:32,999
(The short king has been intimidated by the barbarian.)

828
00:30:33,199 --> 00:30:36,099
If I were the producer...

829
00:30:36,439 --> 00:30:39,109
Remember how Injo was humiliated...

830
00:30:39,509 --> 00:30:41,439
- during the Qing invasion?
- Right.

831
00:30:41,709 --> 00:30:43,808
- Injo's son was very dutiful.
- I see.

832
00:30:43,809 --> 00:30:47,748
"Father, I will get revenge for the scar on your forehead."

833
00:30:47,749 --> 00:30:49,648
It showed his determination to strike the Qing.

834
00:30:49,649 --> 00:30:51,219
- Hyojong.
- Yes, Hyojong.

835
00:30:51,589 --> 00:30:55,089
- Hyojong had a good build.
- Kang Hyojong.

836
00:30:55,459 --> 00:30:58,328
Ho Dong defeated many opponents with his body.

837
00:30:58,329 --> 00:31:00,759
Because of Hyojong's great build,

838
00:31:01,059 --> 00:31:02,899
his shoulders got caught...

839
00:31:03,099 --> 00:31:04,829
in the coffin when he passed away.

840
00:31:06,099 --> 00:31:07,169
The coffin?

841
00:31:07,569 --> 00:31:08,869
The coffin was remade.

842
00:31:09,869 --> 00:31:11,568
- Was I Joseon's...
- Hyojong.

843
00:31:11,569 --> 00:31:12,638
- Hyojong.
- Yes.

844
00:31:12,639 --> 00:31:14,939
Does that mean Ho Dong will have to act like this?

845
00:31:15,679 --> 00:31:18,178
- Then...
- His shoulders are too wide.

846
00:31:18,179 --> 00:31:21,018
Historically speaking, I also have a king I could play.

847
00:31:21,019 --> 00:31:22,119
Seongjong.

848
00:31:22,679 --> 00:31:25,089
He was the tallest king in the Joseon Dynasty.

849
00:31:25,819 --> 00:31:27,158
He was the tallest,

850
00:31:27,159 --> 00:31:29,559
and according to the records,

851
00:31:30,189 --> 00:31:34,328
his subjects always asked, "How are you so tall?"

852
00:31:34,329 --> 00:31:35,728
Back then, wasn’t anyone over 170cm considered tall?

853
00:31:35,729 --> 00:31:37,798
It wasn't that much. The records say that...

854
00:31:37,799 --> 00:31:38,828
Really?

855
00:31:38,829 --> 00:31:40,498
his subjects would always ask,

856
00:31:40,499 --> 00:31:41,668
- "How are you so tall,"
- Then, he must be...

857
00:31:41,669 --> 00:31:42,798
- "Your Highness?"
- even taller.

858
00:31:42,799 --> 00:31:44,608
- For Jang Hoon, - He must have been...

859
00:31:44,609 --> 00:31:46,269
his legs will hang out of his casket.

860
00:31:47,809 --> 00:31:50,909
That will happen for Jang Hoon.

861
00:31:52,279 --> 00:31:53,679
Next is...

862
00:31:53,919 --> 00:31:56,119
the second common trait of the transfer students.

863
00:31:56,449 --> 00:31:58,318
They all majored in Theater and Film.

864
00:31:58,319 --> 00:32:00,689
I get it for Min Woo and Tae Woo,

865
00:32:01,089 --> 00:32:03,789
but why did you major in that, Min Seok?

866
00:32:04,029 --> 00:32:05,589
- My childhood dream...
- Yes?

867
00:32:05,989 --> 00:32:07,459
was to be William Shakespeare.

868
00:32:08,299 --> 00:32:09,828
Anyone can dream.

869
00:32:09,829 --> 00:32:11,098
I wanted to write, direct,

870
00:32:11,099 --> 00:32:12,828
- and act as well.
- Sure.

871
00:32:12,829 --> 00:32:16,069
Even when I was in school, I always wrote scripts in class,

872
00:32:16,599 --> 00:32:19,069
and had "Othello" in my hand.

873
00:32:19,839 --> 00:32:21,508
I got into Dankook University's...

874
00:32:21,509 --> 00:32:23,239
Department of Theater and Film at 25,

875
00:32:23,549 --> 00:32:24,779
and I went to school with Yoo Ji Tae,

876
00:32:25,209 --> 00:32:26,708
although he entered later than me.

877
00:32:26,709 --> 00:32:27,778
Yoo Ji Tae and Ha Ji Won.

878
00:32:27,779 --> 00:32:29,418
- He played Han Myong Hoe.
- Han Myong Hoe.

879
00:32:29,419 --> 00:32:31,248
- Yes, Han Myong Hoe.
- Yoo Ji Tae.

880
00:32:31,249 --> 00:32:32,988
He played that.

881
00:32:32,989 --> 00:32:35,489
There were so many handsome and pretty people at school,

882
00:32:36,019 --> 00:32:37,389
but those two were different.

883
00:32:37,729 --> 00:32:39,159
They were so diligent.

884
00:32:39,959 --> 00:32:41,099
So very much.

885
00:32:41,199 --> 00:32:42,899
Ji Tae practically lived on campus.

886
00:32:43,259 --> 00:32:46,498
In the end, those who are diligent and sincere...

887
00:32:46,499 --> 00:32:48,538
- end up making it.
- Sure.

888
00:32:48,539 --> 00:32:51,038
Then how did you end up becoming a history teacher?

889
00:32:51,039 --> 00:32:53,739
- You majored in Theater and Film.
- I didn't like history.

890
00:32:54,109 --> 00:32:55,308
How could anyone like history?

891
00:32:55,309 --> 00:32:58,008
They make you memorize things like "1592, Imjin War, Yi Sun Sin,"

892
00:32:58,009 --> 00:32:59,708
and if you didn't back then, they would hit your palms.

893
00:32:59,709 --> 00:33:01,618
Who would? It's strange if you like that.

894
00:33:01,619 --> 00:33:02,948
- I didn't like it.
- Yes, we got in trouble.

895
00:33:02,949 --> 00:33:05,649
These guys would know, but with Theater and Film,

896
00:33:06,119 --> 00:33:08,319
you can only keep up if you have a dream.

897
00:33:08,919 --> 00:33:10,759
But I got in when I was 25,

898
00:33:10,989 --> 00:33:12,989
and I saw reality instead of my dream.

899
00:33:13,729 --> 00:33:17,329
I was thinking about whether I could make anything work here,

900
00:33:17,599 --> 00:33:21,699
when a history teacher gig came up for five dollars an hour.

901
00:33:21,969 --> 00:33:25,239
Since I was going to teach kids, I needed to study beforehand,

902
00:33:25,569 --> 00:33:27,279
so I went to the library, which I'd never done before...

903
00:33:27,771 --> 00:33:29,171
and read "Baekbumilji,"

904
00:33:29,665 --> 00:33:30,975
"Memoirs of Lady Hyegyong,"

905
00:33:31,549 --> 00:33:33,208
and "Nanjung ilgi,"

906
00:33:33,209 --> 00:33:35,418
- when my perspective opened up.
- Did it?

907
00:33:35,419 --> 00:33:39,348
This is even more solid and tragic...

908
00:33:39,349 --> 00:33:41,188
than the story of William Shakespeare.

909
00:33:41,189 --> 00:33:45,359
Why was this taught to me so boringly all this time?

910
00:33:45,929 --> 00:33:47,698
The whole world changed,

911
00:33:47,699 --> 00:33:51,998
and I used the storytelling skills and logic I learned in school...

912
00:33:51,999 --> 00:33:54,838
as building blocks, connected them,

913
00:33:54,839 --> 00:33:57,138
and laid them out for the children.

914
00:33:57,139 --> 00:34:00,038
It was a whole new world for the kids.

915
00:34:00,039 --> 00:34:01,738
There's acting in Min Seok's lectures.

916
00:34:01,739 --> 00:34:03,508
- Even now.
- You can see it.

917
00:34:03,509 --> 00:34:05,078
- Yes.
- With all the gestures.

918
00:34:05,079 --> 00:34:07,578
That's why it's fun.

919
00:34:07,579 --> 00:34:09,818
- He uses acting and expressions, - Yes.

920
00:34:09,819 --> 00:34:11,718
- which is why the content sinks in.
- Yes.

921
00:34:11,719 --> 00:34:13,348
His lectures even make you cry.

922
00:34:13,349 --> 00:34:15,719
I majored in Theater and Film,

923
00:34:16,089 --> 00:34:18,728
but I took a completely different path...

924
00:34:18,729 --> 00:34:21,059
and I've been a history teacher for 30 years now.

925
00:34:21,729 --> 00:34:23,198
At first, it was a handicap.

926
00:34:23,199 --> 00:34:24,698
It held me back,

927
00:34:24,699 --> 00:34:27,169
and people would talk about my background.

928
00:34:27,699 --> 00:34:31,469
For me, even if I go back,

929
00:34:31,709 --> 00:34:35,079
I will choose Theater and Film over Korean History.

930
00:34:35,379 --> 00:34:39,509
The ways of storytelling and method acting...

931
00:34:39,709 --> 00:34:41,449
that I learned back then...

932
00:34:42,049 --> 00:34:43,918
combined with historical stories...

933
00:34:43,919 --> 00:34:44,919
- to make...
- Yes.

934
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:47,058
("Let me tell you once again that my wish...")

935
00:34:47,059 --> 00:34:49,659
("is for my younger sibling to become king.")

936
00:34:49,959 --> 00:34:52,258
A new style was made,

937
00:34:52,259 --> 00:34:53,758
and thanks to that,

938
00:34:53,759 --> 00:34:56,329
I believe that I am here with you today.

939
00:34:56,799 --> 00:34:58,799
I'm sorry to be asking...

940
00:34:59,169 --> 00:35:00,338
this kind of question now,

941
00:35:00,339 --> 00:35:01,339
but did you graduate?

942
00:35:01,340 --> 00:35:02,638
We don't count dropouts.

943
00:35:02,639 --> 00:35:03,639
(Gosh.)

944
00:35:04,409 --> 00:35:05,409
What about Min Woo?

945
00:35:05,410 --> 00:35:07,108
Min Woo, why are you blinking like that?

946
00:35:07,109 --> 00:35:08,608
You didn't work hard in school, did you?

947
00:35:08,609 --> 00:35:10,079
Didn't you go to Chung-Ang University?

948
00:35:10,479 --> 00:35:11,708
- Did you graduate?
- Did you graduate?

949
00:35:11,709 --> 00:35:12,849
I only graduated from high school.

950
00:35:14,249 --> 00:35:16,318
- Raise your tone for that.
- Come on.

951
00:35:16,319 --> 00:35:18,249
Just proudly say you dropped out.

952
00:35:19,589 --> 00:35:21,658
Why can't you say that you dropped out?

953
00:35:21,659 --> 00:35:23,758
We should do a special for dropouts.

954
00:35:23,759 --> 00:35:25,989
To be exact, I was expelled.

955
00:35:26,289 --> 00:35:27,398
- You were busy, - For lack of academic...

956
00:35:27,399 --> 00:35:28,828
- so you weren't able to go.
- credits.

957
00:35:28,829 --> 00:35:30,668
- You had no time.
- Of course.

958
00:35:30,669 --> 00:35:32,868
- You were acting back then.
- Yes.

959
00:35:32,869 --> 00:35:35,298
We didn't have a management system back then,

960
00:35:35,299 --> 00:35:38,238
and I was the host for "Super Sunday,"

961
00:35:38,239 --> 00:35:40,238
the lead character for a mini series at MBC,

962
00:35:40,239 --> 00:35:41,908
a situation drama at KBS,

963
00:35:41,909 --> 00:35:43,008
"Tears of the Dragon,"

964
00:35:43,009 --> 00:35:45,309
and I also took a leave to be in a play.

965
00:35:45,649 --> 00:35:48,079
That's how 2 to 3 years flew by,

966
00:35:48,449 --> 00:35:50,048
so I failed all my classes.

967
00:35:50,049 --> 00:35:52,048
We have to acknowledge that for you, though.

968
00:35:52,049 --> 00:35:53,758
That's amazing, and I acknowledge it.

969
00:35:53,759 --> 00:35:55,489
- What?
- Your school...

970
00:35:55,789 --> 00:35:57,628
- He's different from you.
- What?

971
00:35:57,629 --> 00:35:58,928
Don't mention Seoul Institute of the Arts.

972
00:35:58,929 --> 00:36:00,828
- Min Woo worked hard.
- Min Woo was expelled.

973
00:36:00,829 --> 00:36:02,498
You were working,

974
00:36:02,499 --> 00:36:04,398
and you were the lead act. He had no choice.

975
00:36:04,399 --> 00:36:06,698
I had no choice, either. It was during "The Angel Who Lost Wings..."

976
00:36:06,699 --> 00:36:07,799
in 1996.

977
00:36:08,539 --> 00:36:09,798
And I dropped out...

978
00:36:09,799 --> 00:36:11,138
before I could get expelled.

979
00:36:11,139 --> 00:36:12,208
- Good job.
- I'm sorry,

980
00:36:12,209 --> 00:36:14,078
- but could you bring the proof?
- There's no proof.

981
00:36:14,079 --> 00:36:15,338
Bring the proof that you got in as the top student.

982
00:36:15,339 --> 00:36:17,008
Bring the proof that you got in as the top student.

983
00:36:17,009 --> 00:36:18,948
- I was the second-ranked.
- "Top student?"

984
00:36:18,949 --> 00:36:21,419
You were top student? I got in as a top student, as well.

985
00:36:21,619 --> 00:36:23,248
You should bring the proof too.

986
00:36:23,249 --> 00:36:25,088
There's a news article. You can search it.

987
00:36:25,089 --> 00:36:26,188
- I was on the news too, - In 1995,

988
00:36:26,189 --> 00:36:27,588
- but I can't find it.
- it was in the social news section.

989
00:36:27,589 --> 00:36:28,688
What about you, Tae Woo?

990
00:36:28,959 --> 00:36:31,758
I was really busy back then, as well.

991
00:36:31,759 --> 00:36:34,258
- After "Emperor Wang Gun" ended, - You look anxious.

992
00:36:34,259 --> 00:36:36,458
- I was doing "New Nonstop, - You did?

993
00:36:36,459 --> 00:36:38,128
and I was also on "Into the Sun..."

994
00:36:38,129 --> 00:36:41,598
- with Kwon Sang Woo.
- And?

995
00:36:41,599 --> 00:36:44,668
I also had a variety show on KBS,

996
00:36:44,669 --> 00:36:46,509
and was a radio DJ,

997
00:36:46,739 --> 00:36:47,908
but I fully graduated.

998
00:36:47,909 --> 00:36:50,579
- What?
- Amazing.

999
00:36:51,009 --> 00:36:52,979
- Really?
- You graduated?

1000
00:36:53,309 --> 00:36:55,218
(I thought he was on our side...)

1001
00:36:55,219 --> 00:36:56,879
You didn't fail at all?

1002
00:36:57,449 --> 00:36:58,888
I did,

1003
00:36:58,889 --> 00:37:00,518
but I retook the class.

1004
00:37:00,519 --> 00:37:02,458
What will happen to Min Woo?

1005
00:37:02,459 --> 00:37:04,229
Why is everyone clapping?

1006
00:37:05,159 --> 00:37:09,398
Min Seok, since you majored in Theater and Film,

1007
00:37:09,399 --> 00:37:12,069
is there any piece that you were in?

1008
00:37:13,839 --> 00:37:16,798
That's the best thing that's ever happened to me.

1009
00:37:16,799 --> 00:37:17,809
I have none at all.

1010
00:37:18,069 --> 00:37:19,069
What?

1011
00:37:19,169 --> 00:37:20,169
None at all?

1012
00:37:20,170 --> 00:37:21,708
If I had any, they would be playing that.

1013
00:37:21,709 --> 00:37:22,908
You don't have any dark moments from the past?

1014
00:37:22,909 --> 00:37:24,378
- None at all.
- We won't find any?

1015
00:37:24,379 --> 00:37:25,708
- It's clean.
- We don't need to?

1016
00:37:25,709 --> 00:37:28,049
He even talks like a theater major.

1017
00:37:28,319 --> 00:37:29,448
He draws attention.

1018
00:37:29,449 --> 00:37:31,248
- He pretends to say something.
- He draws attention.

1019
00:37:31,249 --> 00:37:33,788
He pretends to have something to say.

1020
00:37:33,789 --> 00:37:35,959
If you were cast in something right now,

1021
00:37:36,159 --> 00:37:37,388
is there anything...

1022
00:37:37,389 --> 00:37:38,989
that you always wanted to play?

1023
00:37:39,459 --> 00:37:41,058
I want to be the bad guy.

1024
00:37:41,059 --> 00:37:42,158
- The villain?
- What about Prince Yeonsan?

1025
00:37:42,159 --> 00:37:46,569
Because I'm very playful by nature.

1026
00:37:46,969 --> 00:37:49,069
Just like Ho Dong, I'm very playful.

1027
00:37:49,639 --> 00:37:53,239
I've been a teacher, and a very stern history teacher...

1028
00:37:53,439 --> 00:37:55,939
for the past 30 years,

1029
00:37:56,309 --> 00:37:58,049
so I developed another persona.

1030
00:37:58,479 --> 00:38:00,918
They always tell me to be good,

1031
00:38:00,919 --> 00:38:03,118
and not to do this and that,

1032
00:38:03,119 --> 00:38:06,148
so I want to be a bad person, who is not in their right mind,

1033
00:38:06,149 --> 00:38:08,218
whether it's Prince Yeonsan or Prince Suyang.

1034
00:38:08,219 --> 00:38:09,858
- Your tone will hit just right...
- I know.

1035
00:38:09,859 --> 00:38:11,158
- when you act.
- Yes.

1036
00:38:11,159 --> 00:38:14,858
Min Woo, was the acting environment different in the 1980s and 1990s?

1037
00:38:14,859 --> 00:38:17,399
Yes, it was completely different. A lot of people say,

1038
00:38:17,599 --> 00:38:20,938
"You must have had a hard time, Min Woo,"

1039
00:38:20,939 --> 00:38:23,769
but we didn't have a hard time in the 1980s.

1040
00:38:24,109 --> 00:38:25,409
- When you were younger?
- Really?

1041
00:38:25,709 --> 00:38:27,068
We didn't even have to pull all-nighters.

1042
00:38:27,069 --> 00:38:28,138
There was actually less to do?

1043
00:38:28,139 --> 00:38:29,738
- Since they didn't have equipment?
- In the early 1980s.

1044
00:38:29,739 --> 00:38:31,808
- Yes, we didn't have the equipment.
- They had no equipment.

1045
00:38:31,809 --> 00:38:33,748
- Even if we were shooting outside.
- They can't turn the lights on.

1046
00:38:33,749 --> 00:38:34,848
They had no lights.

1047
00:38:34,849 --> 00:38:36,078
We had no generators,

1048
00:38:36,079 --> 00:38:37,219
so we couldn't turn the lights on.

1049
00:38:38,349 --> 00:38:40,918
So we couldn't shoot for long hours at night.

1050
00:38:40,919 --> 00:38:42,318
It must have ended quickly.

1051
00:38:42,319 --> 00:38:44,129
- And it was post-recorded.
- Yes.

1052
00:38:44,559 --> 00:38:46,028
Even if you don't know all the lines,

1053
00:38:46,029 --> 00:38:47,029
they just let it go.

1054
00:38:47,529 --> 00:38:49,058
We didn't have NG takes back then.

1055
00:38:49,059 --> 00:38:50,398
- They were all okay.
- That's good.

1056
00:38:50,399 --> 00:38:51,768
- We just kept going.
- It was that way.

1057
00:38:51,769 --> 00:38:53,368
We shot 50 to 60 scenes in a day.

1058
00:38:53,369 --> 00:38:55,668
They shot 50 to 60 scenes a day.

1059
00:38:55,669 --> 00:38:56,798
That must have been a lot of lines.

1060
00:38:56,799 --> 00:38:58,538
Even during "Tears of the Dragon,"

1061
00:38:58,539 --> 00:39:02,038
the sound was supposed to be recorded live,

1062
00:39:02,039 --> 00:39:04,478
but the schedule was tight, so the director said,

1063
00:39:04,479 --> 00:39:06,249
"Just shoot it!"

1064
00:39:06,849 --> 00:39:08,378
The sound was post-recorded,

1065
00:39:08,379 --> 00:39:10,049
so we shot 72 scenes in a day.

1066
00:39:10,279 --> 00:39:11,688
(A speed you can’t even imagine today)

1067
00:39:11,689 --> 00:39:15,418
But after the 1988 international games,

1068
00:39:15,419 --> 00:39:16,888
- Did it get more developed?
- which was when...

1069
00:39:16,889 --> 00:39:18,658
- Yes.
- Tae Woo had his debut...

1070
00:39:18,659 --> 00:39:21,228
I happened to debut at the worst possible time.

1071
00:39:21,229 --> 00:39:23,458
- That was when...
- Technology suddenly improved.

1072
00:39:23,459 --> 00:39:26,028
- There was improvement, - It divides into before and after.

1073
00:39:26,029 --> 00:39:28,098
but that was when it started to get complicated for us.

1074
00:39:28,099 --> 00:39:30,099
- We could shoot all night.
- The equipment improved,

1075
00:39:30,569 --> 00:39:32,239
so we could shoot all night.

1076
00:39:32,739 --> 00:39:34,708
And technology developed even more,

1077
00:39:34,709 --> 00:39:37,348
and ten years after that during "The Princess's Man,"

1078
00:39:37,349 --> 00:39:39,678
we would shoot up to an hour before airing.

1079
00:39:39,679 --> 00:39:41,278
- Gosh.
- We would shoot.

1080
00:39:41,279 --> 00:39:43,418
Then it was practically going out live?

1081
00:39:43,419 --> 00:39:45,988
Everything else was edited beforehand...

1082
00:39:45,989 --> 00:39:47,118
Just the last scene...

1083
00:39:47,119 --> 00:39:48,158
- that was left out.
- The last scene...

1084
00:39:48,159 --> 00:39:49,458
would be sent to the staff,

1085
00:39:49,459 --> 00:39:52,558
and they would edit it...

1086
00:39:52,559 --> 00:39:54,598
- right on the spot.
- That's tense.

1087
00:39:54,599 --> 00:39:55,829
And as it is airing,

1088
00:39:56,159 --> 00:39:58,028
they would have it ready, and when it ends,

1089
00:39:58,029 --> 00:39:59,228
they would play the next one right away.

1090
00:39:59,229 --> 00:40:01,699
Gosh, they would be in trouble if they made a mistake.

1091
00:40:02,239 --> 00:40:06,208
These days, the environment and conditions are so good,

1092
00:40:06,209 --> 00:40:07,438
- The environment these days...
- so back then...

1093
00:40:07,439 --> 00:40:09,378
If you were to ask if I would go back 40 years ago...

1094
00:40:09,379 --> 00:40:12,908
and do it again under those conditions,

1095
00:40:12,909 --> 00:40:14,719
- I don't think I would.
- It's so difficult.

1096
00:40:15,049 --> 00:40:17,049
- What about Min Seok?
- If you were born again.

1097
00:40:18,489 --> 00:40:19,989
For me,

1098
00:40:20,249 --> 00:40:23,259
even if I were born 100 or 1,000 times,

1099
00:40:23,789 --> 00:40:24,988
I would choose this path again.

1100
00:40:24,989 --> 00:40:27,328
- Gosh.
- Even his tone stands out.

1101
00:40:27,329 --> 00:40:28,858
His timing stands out.

1102
00:40:28,859 --> 00:40:30,828
Speak more naturally, Min Seok.

1103
00:40:30,829 --> 00:40:32,428
We just asked a question and...

1104
00:40:32,429 --> 00:40:33,728
"Hundred..."

1105
00:40:33,729 --> 00:40:34,798
- "or thousand times..."
- "Thousand times."

1106
00:40:34,799 --> 00:40:36,168
Come on.

1107
00:40:36,169 --> 00:40:37,808
- Your whole life is an act.
- Come on.

1108
00:40:37,809 --> 00:40:39,068
We were just...

1109
00:40:39,069 --> 00:40:40,908
I’m too uncomfortable to ask any questions.

1110
00:40:40,909 --> 00:40:42,009
We really need...

1111
00:40:42,379 --> 00:40:44,078
to learn from Min Seok.

1112
00:40:44,079 --> 00:40:45,248
- I know.
- I mean...

1113
00:40:45,249 --> 00:40:47,618
- His flow is pure art.
- It's all acting.

1114
00:40:47,619 --> 00:40:49,078
He draws everyone's attention...

1115
00:40:49,079 --> 00:40:51,218
- before getting to the conclusion.
- Yes.

1116
00:40:51,219 --> 00:40:53,549
You need to pause between 100 and 1,000.

1117
00:40:53,889 --> 00:40:55,388
- Yes.
- Cue.

1118
00:40:55,389 --> 00:40:57,058
- "Even if I were born hundred..."
- "Thousand."

1119
00:40:57,059 --> 00:40:58,358
"or 1,000 times..."

1120
00:40:58,359 --> 00:41:00,088
- It has to be like this.
- Why are you like a henchman?

1121
00:41:00,089 --> 00:41:01,099
Right?

1122
00:41:01,359 --> 00:41:02,458
(Not everyone can use this method style.)

1123
00:41:02,459 --> 00:41:05,969
Min Seok, you have a way with words.

1124
00:41:06,229 --> 00:41:08,038
- They have a nice ring to them.
- Yes, they do.

1125
00:41:08,039 --> 00:41:11,408
Were you born with it?

1126
00:41:11,409 --> 00:41:14,438
Or did your majoring in Theater and Film help?

1127
00:41:14,439 --> 00:41:15,609
Ever since I was young,

1128
00:41:16,079 --> 00:41:18,748
I was good at taking part in school events,

1129
00:41:18,749 --> 00:41:20,779
and was good at acting as well. But...

1130
00:41:21,449 --> 00:41:23,949
I have very strong J traits in the MBTI.

1131
00:41:24,389 --> 00:41:28,259
So when I have a lecture for shows like "History Tellers,"

1132
00:41:28,689 --> 00:41:31,189
I have the same rehearsals five times.

1133
00:41:31,989 --> 00:41:33,328
- That's amazing.
- Just the rehearsals?

1134
00:41:33,329 --> 00:41:35,898
I have the rehearsals five times.

1135
00:41:35,899 --> 00:41:38,329
(The outcome of relentless practice to give a flawless lecture)

1136
00:41:39,969 --> 00:41:41,368
You are all born with your talent,

1137
00:41:41,369 --> 00:41:43,739
whether it's ssireum, basketball, or music.

1138
00:41:44,309 --> 00:41:47,339
But I believe that what really makes the difference...

1139
00:41:47,679 --> 00:41:49,778
is the passion that goes beyond effort.

1140
00:41:49,779 --> 00:41:51,609
(Gosh.)

1141
00:41:51,879 --> 00:41:52,978
His words...

1142
00:41:52,979 --> 00:41:54,449
- But...
- It's not funny,

1143
00:41:54,749 --> 00:41:56,149
but it really sticks with you.

1144
00:41:56,379 --> 00:41:57,948
It just sticks, right?

1145
00:41:57,949 --> 00:42:01,888
- He has a way of charming...
- Right.

1146
00:42:01,889 --> 00:42:02,988
- the listeners.
- That's right.

1147
00:42:02,989 --> 00:42:06,358
- He has that timing and tone.
- It feels like a sin...

1148
00:42:06,359 --> 00:42:08,799
not to pay attention to him.

1149
00:42:08,859 --> 00:42:10,769
(His speech is on another level.)

1150
00:42:10,999 --> 00:42:13,769
Lastly, we have...

1151
00:42:14,339 --> 00:42:16,899
a presentation class. This...

1152
00:42:17,239 --> 00:42:20,109
was specially prepared by Min Seok. Isn't that right?

1153
00:42:20,439 --> 00:42:22,009
- We met Danjong, - Danjong.

1154
00:42:22,379 --> 00:42:25,349
a tragic figure in history, as today’s topic.

1155
00:42:25,949 --> 00:42:28,519
The film about him became a phenomenon,

1156
00:42:28,919 --> 00:42:31,218
sparking curiosity among many people.

1157
00:42:31,219 --> 00:42:35,258
I prepared a talk about Danjong...

1158
00:42:35,259 --> 00:42:37,829
where people who watched the movie can reflect on that time once more,

1159
00:42:38,729 --> 00:42:40,488
and those who haven't can still gain some knowledge.

1160
00:42:40,489 --> 00:42:41,698
(Today's lecture will help you understand Danjong more easily...)

1161
00:42:41,699 --> 00:42:42,898
(and in greater depth.)

1162
00:42:42,899 --> 00:42:44,669
This is going to be fun!

1163
00:42:45,229 --> 00:42:48,369
(The unfinished story of Danjong)

1164
00:42:48,899 --> 00:42:49,969
The start...

1165
00:42:51,369 --> 00:42:53,809
of all this tragedy...

1166
00:42:54,579 --> 00:42:55,708
was love.

1167
00:42:55,709 --> 00:42:58,778
- Love.
- It's always love.

1168
00:42:58,779 --> 00:43:02,679
(Love, the seed of Danjong’s tragedy)

1169
00:43:03,219 --> 00:43:06,089
It was the love of a king who...

1170
00:43:06,819 --> 00:43:08,359
cared too deeply for his people...

1171
00:43:08,819 --> 00:43:11,129
that ultimately brought about this tragedy.

1172
00:43:11,189 --> 00:43:14,728
We've looked at Danjong as a figure...

1173
00:43:14,729 --> 00:43:17,159
in movies or history.

1174
00:43:17,299 --> 00:43:19,899
We've been focusing on that one flower that never got to bloom.

1175
00:43:20,329 --> 00:43:22,199
But if we step back a little, what else can we see?

1176
00:43:22,639 --> 00:43:23,739
We can see the tree.

1177
00:43:24,139 --> 00:43:25,709
If we step further back, we can see the forest.

1178
00:43:26,009 --> 00:43:27,339
If we step further back, what do we see?

1179
00:43:27,439 --> 00:43:28,679
- We can see the mountain range.
- Yes.

1180
00:43:28,939 --> 00:43:31,378
The same thing applies here. We shouldn't just focus on Danjong.

1181
00:43:31,379 --> 00:43:33,648
We should look at the era, the circumstances,

1182
00:43:33,649 --> 00:43:34,979
and the history to understand why...

1183
00:43:35,749 --> 00:43:37,848
- he had to go through what he did.
- Right.

1184
00:43:37,849 --> 00:43:39,088
- Are you all ready?
- Yes.

1185
00:43:39,089 --> 00:43:40,989
Yes. We are ready.

1186
00:43:42,189 --> 00:43:43,288
Let's get into it.

1187
00:43:43,289 --> 00:43:44,389
Let's get into it.

1188
00:43:45,629 --> 00:43:47,459
- Teacher.
- Hee Chul.

1189
00:43:47,659 --> 00:43:49,759
Is this how it usually goes?

1190
00:43:50,359 --> 00:43:52,368
- This is like...
- Whispering.

1191
00:43:52,369 --> 00:43:55,768
Why do you think Danjong...

1192
00:43:55,769 --> 00:43:57,099
had a tragic death?

1193
00:43:58,509 --> 00:43:59,569
Why?

1194
00:43:59,639 --> 00:44:01,778
- Because he had no power.
- Why didn't he have power?

1195
00:44:01,779 --> 00:44:02,838
He was young.

1196
00:44:02,839 --> 00:44:04,009
He was young. Good.

1197
00:44:04,109 --> 00:44:05,508
He had no protector.

1198
00:44:05,509 --> 00:44:07,479
- He had no guardian.
- Good.

1199
00:44:07,549 --> 00:44:09,678
- Danjong...
- His grandfather and grandmother...

1200
00:44:09,679 --> 00:44:12,188
Danjong became a king at a young age.

1201
00:44:12,189 --> 00:44:13,649
Why did he become king at a young age?

1202
00:44:13,819 --> 00:44:15,618
- His father died at an early age.
- That's right.

1203
00:44:15,619 --> 00:44:17,058
- Who was his father?
- Mun...

1204
00:44:17,059 --> 00:44:18,328
- Munjong.
- Yes.

1205
00:44:18,329 --> 00:44:21,459
This happened because Munjong died at an early age.

1206
00:44:22,229 --> 00:44:23,358
- Right?
- Yes.

1207
00:44:23,359 --> 00:44:26,569
Munjong here, used to be healthy.

1208
00:44:26,999 --> 00:44:28,799
First of all, he looked like Kim Hee Chul.

1209
00:44:29,169 --> 00:44:30,268
(Munjong, 5th king of the Joseon, known for his handsome appearance)

1210
00:44:30,269 --> 00:44:32,309
- He was handsome.
- He had Kyung Hoon's skin.

1211
00:44:33,069 --> 00:44:35,408
The Annals of the Joseon Dynasty rarely recorded...

1212
00:44:35,409 --> 00:44:37,749
a king's physical appearance.

1213
00:44:38,349 --> 00:44:40,179
It said he had skin like jade...

1214
00:44:40,379 --> 00:44:41,519
and was well-built.

1215
00:44:41,679 --> 00:44:45,548
Munjong was a name given to him after his death.

1216
00:44:45,549 --> 00:44:46,619
The name on his grave.

1217
00:44:46,749 --> 00:44:48,088
It means he studied well.

1218
00:44:48,089 --> 00:44:49,819
- Mun, meaning literature.
- That's right.

1219
00:44:51,089 --> 00:44:52,288
(The six arts, calendrical science and celestial observation, )

1220
00:44:52,289 --> 00:44:53,458
(phonology, astronomy, music theory)

1221
00:44:53,459 --> 00:44:54,798
(There was nothing he had not mastered.)

1222
00:44:54,799 --> 00:44:55,958
(From the Annals of King Munjong)

1223
00:44:55,959 --> 00:44:57,769
He excelled in both literature and martial arts.

1224
00:44:58,029 --> 00:44:59,229
He was a healthy man.

1225
