1467
00:54:05,479 --> 00:54:07,408
- Seo Myong Hoe?
- Hey, Myong Hoe.

1468
00:54:07,409 --> 00:54:09,648
- I'm Prince Suyang.
- Hey, Myong Hoe.

1469
00:54:09,649 --> 00:54:11,518
- I think we are bound by fate.
- So...

1470
00:54:11,519 --> 00:54:13,188
You know what I'd want to do.

1471
00:54:13,189 --> 00:54:15,359
Do I have the face of someone destined for divorce?

1472
00:54:15,459 --> 00:54:16,588
(He has both money and the characteristic of Myong Hoe.)

1473
00:54:16,589 --> 00:54:18,488
- The actor...
- He's Myong Hoe.

1474
00:54:18,489 --> 00:54:20,258
So, which of you is Han Myong Hoe today?

1475
00:54:20,259 --> 00:54:21,799
- It's Seo Jang Hoon.
- Seo Jang Hoon.

1476
00:54:22,359 --> 00:54:25,329
And Jang Hoon is good at persuading.

1477
00:54:25,529 --> 00:54:26,729
"Prince Suyang, come here."

1478
00:54:27,199 --> 00:54:28,599
"Just listen to what I say!"

1479
00:54:29,469 --> 00:54:30,998
- He's like that.
- "Don't you want to be the king?"

1480
00:54:30,999 --> 00:54:32,138
(Seo Myong Hoe is a pacifist.)

1481
00:54:32,139 --> 00:54:33,169
Seo Myong Hoe.

1482
00:54:33,339 --> 00:54:35,008
Seo Jang Hoon is selected as Han Myong Hoe.

1483
00:54:35,009 --> 00:54:36,039
Yes.

1484
00:54:36,939 --> 00:54:40,108
Am I supposed to be happy about it?

1485
00:54:40,109 --> 00:54:41,679
He's a historical figure, after all.

1486
00:54:41,879 --> 00:54:45,748
The person who brought Han Myong Hoe and Prince Suyang together...

1487
00:54:45,749 --> 00:54:47,889
- is a man named Kwon Ram.
- Right.

1488
00:54:48,619 --> 00:54:49,958
Here's the thing about Kwon Ram.

1489
00:54:49,959 --> 00:54:52,729
He co-wrote a military treatise with Prince Suyang.

1490
00:54:52,929 --> 00:54:54,328
(Yeokdae Byeongyo: A military strategy book...)

1491
00:54:54,329 --> 00:54:55,998
(that compiles major war cases to analyze...)

1492
00:54:55,999 --> 00:54:57,699
(the causes of victory and defeat and tactics)

1493
00:54:58,029 --> 00:55:00,599
Prince Suyang would get annoyed whenever they met,

1494
00:55:00,799 --> 00:55:02,339
so Kwon Ram said this.

1495
00:55:03,069 --> 00:55:06,309
"Your Highness, would you like to meet someone?"

1496
00:55:07,269 --> 00:55:08,379
"Who is it?"

1497
00:55:08,979 --> 00:55:11,679
"He has been my friend since childhood."

1498
00:55:11,949 --> 00:55:13,279
"His name is Myong Hoe."

1499
00:55:14,409 --> 00:55:16,718
"He comes from a good family, but he isn't academically gifted."

1500
00:55:16,719 --> 00:55:17,849
"Still, he's very quick-witted."

1501
00:55:18,119 --> 00:55:20,248
"Thanks to his family's benevolence, he obtained an official post,"

1502
00:55:20,249 --> 00:55:21,489
"but he is currently serving as a palace guard."

1503
00:55:21,859 --> 00:55:23,489
"He has a sense of lack."

1504
00:55:23,559 --> 00:55:25,589
"And one day, he told me this."

1505
00:55:25,959 --> 00:55:27,688
"There is a good path for Prince Suyang."

1506
00:55:27,689 --> 00:55:29,099
"Let me meet him just once."

1507
00:55:29,629 --> 00:55:30,959
"Would you like to meet him?"

1508
00:55:32,399 --> 00:55:34,168
- This is what happened.
- That's how they met.

1509
00:55:34,169 --> 00:55:35,968
Then Han Myong Hoe came to him.

1510
00:55:35,969 --> 00:55:37,868
- He was like this.
- "What?"

1511
00:55:37,869 --> 00:55:41,239
As soon as Prince Suyang saw him, he ran over and took his hand.

1512
00:55:42,179 --> 00:55:43,839
"You have the face of a hero!"

1513
00:55:44,139 --> 00:55:47,979
Upon hearing this, Han Myong Hoe greeted him and began to talk.

1514
00:55:48,049 --> 00:55:50,618
I have a question for Jang Hoon. You're Han Myong Hoe now.

1515
00:55:50,619 --> 00:55:52,149
Let's say you just met Prince Suyang.

1516
00:55:52,349 --> 00:55:55,659
You know what you intend to do.

1517
00:55:55,819 --> 00:55:57,759
But would you tell Prince Suyang about it the moment you met him?

1518
00:55:57,919 --> 00:56:00,328
- It'd be too difficult to do that.
- How could you say that right away?

1519
00:56:00,329 --> 00:56:01,659
- It's the first day.
- You can't do that.

1520
00:56:01,899 --> 00:56:03,528
- It's a revolt.
- They should drink.

1521
00:56:03,529 --> 00:56:04,529
- Exactly.
- He can't do it...

1522
00:56:04,530 --> 00:56:05,569
unless they drink each other.

1523
00:56:06,069 --> 00:56:09,369
But Han Myong Hoe said that the moment they met.

1524
00:56:10,969 --> 00:56:12,709
Jang Hoon will read the Annals of the Joseon Dynasty.

1525
00:56:14,009 --> 00:56:16,378
This is what Han Myong Hoe told Prince Suyang...

1526
00:56:16,379 --> 00:56:18,879
the day he met him. Read it with emotion.

1527
00:56:19,609 --> 00:56:21,009
You should sit.

1528
00:56:21,249 --> 00:56:23,678
- Jang Hoon, are you ready?
- Sit.

1529
00:56:23,679 --> 00:56:25,089
- This is higher.
- Action.

1530
00:56:26,149 --> 00:56:30,359
"When the king was young, unrighteous people seized power,"

1531
00:56:30,659 --> 00:56:32,359
"and when they took power,"

1532
00:56:32,729 --> 00:56:35,699
"wicked factions brought about the calamity of misfortune."

1533
00:56:36,229 --> 00:56:40,099
"It was only after a loyal minister appeared..."

1534
00:56:40,569 --> 00:56:42,199
"and staged a coup..."

1535
00:56:42,439 --> 00:56:44,498
"that all these problems were resolved."

1536
00:56:44,499 --> 00:56:48,069
"This is the natural order of things."

1537
00:56:50,279 --> 00:56:51,338
What are you?

1538
00:56:51,339 --> 00:56:53,079
- Prince Suyang didn't understand.
- How dare you!

1539
00:56:53,179 --> 00:56:55,178
- He didn't understand.
- Are you Prince Suyang?

1540
00:56:55,179 --> 00:56:56,649
No, I'm Soo Geun.

1541
00:56:57,919 --> 00:56:58,919
I'm sorry.

1542
00:57:00,719 --> 00:57:03,988
(The end of the drama featuring Lee Suyang and Seo Myong Hoe)

1543
00:57:03,989 --> 00:57:06,689
- How could he say that right away?
- That's impressive.

1544
00:57:07,559 --> 00:57:09,828
- He was determined.
- He just said that right away.

1545
00:57:09,829 --> 00:57:12,269
So the two of them agreed with each other.

1546
00:57:12,669 --> 00:57:13,868
- They really hit it off.
- That's right.

1547
00:57:13,869 --> 00:57:15,298
History shows that...

1548
00:57:15,299 --> 00:57:17,539
people with deficiencies tend to band together like this.

1549
00:57:18,169 --> 00:57:19,209
- Deficiencies.
- Yes.

1550
00:57:19,509 --> 00:57:21,169
So, they hit it off that day.

1551
00:57:21,909 --> 00:57:24,279
To put it in their own words, they plotted a grand undertaking.

1552
00:57:24,809 --> 00:57:26,979
So, this is how they divided the roles.

1553
00:57:27,079 --> 00:57:29,149
This is what Han Myong Hoe did.

1554
00:57:29,319 --> 00:57:31,748
He recruited the close associates of Kim Chong So and Hwangbo In,

1555
00:57:31,749 --> 00:57:33,589
who were to be eliminated.

1556
00:57:34,149 --> 00:57:36,119
He needed to know their locations and movements.

1557
00:57:36,359 --> 00:57:38,458
After that, he began recruiting soldiers...

1558
00:57:38,459 --> 00:57:42,298
to join them on the day of the coup.

1559
00:57:42,299 --> 00:57:43,359
(Han Myong Hoe recruited soldiers.)

1560
00:57:43,729 --> 00:57:45,669
What did Prince Suyang do?

1561
00:57:46,499 --> 00:57:47,629
He met with the King.

1562
00:57:48,369 --> 00:57:51,809
"Your Majesty, now you have become King."

1563
00:57:51,909 --> 00:57:55,109
"You know we must go to the Ming Dynasty to seek permission."

1564
00:57:56,009 --> 00:57:57,839
"I will go as the envoy."

1565
00:57:58,509 --> 00:57:59,878
(Gomyeong Saeunsa: An envoy sent to pay respects...)

1566
00:57:59,879 --> 00:58:01,308
(to the Ming Dynasty, which approved...)

1567
00:58:01,309 --> 00:58:02,718
(the enthronement of the King of Joseon)

1568
00:58:02,719 --> 00:58:06,249
Danjong said, "Why would you go there?"

1569
00:58:06,419 --> 00:58:07,549
"You don't have to."

1570
00:58:07,819 --> 00:58:11,218
"Your Majesty, I have no interest in politics."

1571
00:58:11,219 --> 00:58:13,129
- That's what he said?
- "I'll go there,"

1572
00:58:13,659 --> 00:58:15,699
"speak well of Your Majesty,"

1573
00:58:16,029 --> 00:58:18,198
"and pay my respect." He said that.

1574
00:58:18,199 --> 00:58:19,498
(Your Majesty is young, )

1575
00:58:19,499 --> 00:58:21,028
(and while the ministers plan and discuss the affairs of the court, )

1576
00:58:21,029 --> 00:58:22,638
(we have nothing to do here, )

1577
00:58:22,639 --> 00:58:24,039
(so I request to go as an envoy.)

1578
00:58:24,099 --> 00:58:26,809
So, listen. Once he goes as an envoy,

1579
00:58:26,909 --> 00:58:29,378
Danjong and Kim Chong So will feel at ease.

1580
00:58:29,379 --> 00:58:30,439
That is one reason.

1581
00:58:30,679 --> 00:58:31,849
What is the second reason?

1582
00:58:32,209 --> 00:58:34,049
When he becomes the next king,

1583
00:58:34,549 --> 00:58:37,079
he will have to obtain permission from the Ming Emperor anyway.

1584
00:58:37,849 --> 00:58:39,519
- So he intended to go in advance...
- To flatter him.

1585
00:58:39,619 --> 00:58:41,189
to establish ties.

1586
00:58:41,619 --> 00:58:42,719
That's clever.

1587
00:58:43,419 --> 00:58:44,759
So he went.

1588
00:58:45,029 --> 00:58:47,328
After he returned, the day arrived.

1589
00:58:47,329 --> 00:58:51,529
It was October 10, 1453.

1590
00:58:52,829 --> 00:58:54,899
It was the year of Gyeyu.

1591
00:58:56,199 --> 00:58:57,899
- Gyeyu Coup.
- That's right.

1592
00:58:58,099 --> 00:58:59,808
It was October 10 of the year of Gyeyu.

1593
00:58:59,809 --> 00:59:03,038
Everyone gathered at the house of Prince Suyang.

1594
00:59:03,039 --> 00:59:04,108
(Han Myong Hoe and the soldiers gathered at Prince Suyang's house.)

1595
00:59:04,109 --> 00:59:06,148
The soldiers with swords...

1596
00:59:06,149 --> 00:59:07,749
and Han Myong Hoe were there.

1597
00:59:08,179 --> 00:59:09,649
And the soldiers with swords.

1598
00:59:10,119 --> 00:59:12,019
Prince Suyang made up his mind.

1599
00:59:12,289 --> 00:59:15,158
What is the essential requirement for all revolutions and coups?

1600
00:59:15,159 --> 00:59:16,159
- Reason.
- People.

1601
00:59:16,160 --> 00:59:17,788
People are important, but there is something even more important.

1602
00:59:17,789 --> 00:59:20,859
- Justification.
- Exactly. He needs a justification.

1603
00:59:20,989 --> 00:59:23,058
Why they are staging a coup.

1604
00:59:23,059 --> 00:59:24,558
So, this is the reason they came up with.

1605
00:59:24,559 --> 00:59:25,869
It's the year of Gyeyu.

1606
00:59:26,529 --> 00:59:28,399
"Prince Anpyeong right here..."

1607
00:59:28,939 --> 00:59:32,509
"is bribing the wicked Kim Chong So and Hwangbo In..."

1608
00:59:32,809 --> 00:59:34,539
"to harm our King Danjong."

1609
00:59:35,279 --> 00:59:37,279
"This is a rebellion."

1610
00:59:38,079 --> 00:59:41,008
"We will suppress this rebellion."

1611
00:59:41,009 --> 00:59:43,078
(Gyeyu Coup)

1612
00:59:43,079 --> 00:59:44,848
This is why it's called Gyeyu Coup.

1613
00:59:44,849 --> 00:59:45,988
(Under the pretext of quelling the rebellion and bringing peace, )

1614
00:59:45,989 --> 00:59:47,088
(Prince Suyang and Han Myong Hoe eliminated the faction...)

1615
00:59:47,089 --> 00:59:48,289
(of Kim Chong So and Hwangbo In and seized power.)

1616
00:59:48,889 --> 00:59:50,418
It was a fabricated justification.

1617
00:59:50,419 --> 00:59:51,458
(A frame-up disguised as a justification)

1618
00:59:51,459 --> 00:59:53,829
Who do you think Prince Suyang should strike first?

1619
00:59:54,089 --> 00:59:55,529
- Kim Chong So.
- It is Kim Chong So.

1620
00:59:55,799 --> 00:59:59,469
He said, "We will go and strike Kim Chong So."

1621
01:00:00,029 --> 01:00:02,899
Just then, a warrior grabbed Prince Suyang's arm.

1622
01:00:03,499 --> 01:00:06,069
"No. You can't go."

1623
01:00:06,109 --> 01:00:08,269
"What are you talking about? We need to start the mission."

1624
01:00:10,339 --> 01:00:13,349
"You need to go to His Majesty and receive his approval first."

1625
01:00:13,809 --> 01:00:15,879
"If we act without His Majesty's approval,"

1626
01:00:16,179 --> 01:00:18,349
- "this is treason."
- It's treason.

1627
01:00:19,989 --> 01:00:21,789
"What if he doesn't approve?"

1628
01:00:22,289 --> 01:00:23,719
"Then, we will be annihilated."

1629
01:00:23,919 --> 01:00:27,459
"We will get rid of Kim Chong So, and then receive his approval."

1630
01:00:27,559 --> 01:00:30,398
"No." This is how they were split into factions.

1631
01:00:30,399 --> 01:00:31,798
(A conflict of opinion arising from the order of obtaining approval)

1632
01:00:31,799 --> 01:00:33,029
On the day of the grand undertaking.

1633
01:00:34,169 --> 01:00:35,539
What do they do?

1634
01:00:36,969 --> 01:00:38,269
What would you do?

1635
01:00:39,539 --> 01:00:42,209
Actually, I would get approval first.

1636
01:00:42,909 --> 01:00:44,209
- Approval first, - Exactly.

1637
01:00:44,539 --> 01:00:45,578
- action later.
- Yes.

1638
01:00:45,579 --> 01:00:47,448
Then, there will be no trouble later.

1639
01:00:47,449 --> 01:00:48,979
But what if Danjong doesn't approve?

1640
01:00:49,779 --> 01:00:51,678
- Danjong is young.
- He's young.

1641
01:00:51,679 --> 01:00:53,089
I would try talking to him...

1642
01:00:53,249 --> 01:00:55,389
in various ways. I would even yell at him.

1643
01:00:55,489 --> 01:00:58,088
Then dawn would break, and the words would spread.

1644
01:00:58,089 --> 01:01:00,189
- They would return to their homes.
- That's what happens.

1645
01:01:00,659 --> 01:01:02,799
"Let's pretend this never happened!"

1646
01:01:03,029 --> 01:01:04,399
"Enjoy your meal."

1647
01:01:05,099 --> 01:01:07,699
But think about it the other way around, Kyung Hoon.

1648
01:01:07,999 --> 01:01:10,769
Let's say you strike Kim Chong So without the king's approval.

1649
01:01:10,939 --> 01:01:13,869
That's not all. There is also the public sentiment.

1650
01:01:14,669 --> 01:01:16,708
This is a rebellion.

1651
01:01:16,709 --> 01:01:18,678
But didn't they decide on it in advance...

1652
01:01:18,679 --> 01:01:21,279
while preparing for such a huge mission?

1653
01:01:21,779 --> 01:01:22,949
It's too spontaneous.

1654
01:01:23,449 --> 01:01:25,188
- It's like...
- You can split into two groups.

1655
01:01:25,189 --> 01:01:26,818
Suyang should go to Danjong...

1656
01:01:26,819 --> 01:01:28,389
while Han Myong Hoe...

1657
01:01:28,919 --> 01:01:30,158
should go to strike Kim Chong So.

1658
01:01:30,159 --> 01:01:32,028
We can do that now.

1659
01:01:32,029 --> 01:01:33,828
- The opposing party...
- But back then,

1660
01:01:33,829 --> 01:01:37,298
it would've been difficult to carry things out simultaneously.

1661
01:01:37,299 --> 01:01:39,799
It's not like they could use radio and ask how things were going.

1662
01:01:39,829 --> 01:01:41,529
It was impossible back then.

1663
01:01:42,099 --> 01:01:44,469
Since Prince Suyang was at a disadvantage,

1664
01:01:44,739 --> 01:01:48,538
he likely had no choice but to strike Kim Chong So first,

1665
01:01:48,539 --> 01:01:53,249
even if it meant taking a risk.

1666
01:01:53,979 --> 01:01:55,548
Han Myong Hoe made that decision.

1667
01:01:55,549 --> 01:01:57,449
You're Han Myong Hoe himself.

1668
01:01:58,479 --> 01:01:59,919
It's the resurrection of Han Myong Hoe.

1669
01:02:00,219 --> 01:02:01,789
Han Myong Hoe is back.

1670
01:02:01,989 --> 01:02:05,188
For your information, Han Myong Hoe would later...

1671
01:02:05,189 --> 01:02:09,758
serve the kings for three generations.

1672
01:02:09,759 --> 01:02:11,228
(Sejo, Yejong, and Seongjong)

1673
01:02:11,229 --> 01:02:12,729
(A key figure in power spanning 3 generations)

1674
01:02:13,369 --> 01:02:17,638
There is a pavilion named after Han Myong Hoe in Apgujeong.

1675
01:02:17,639 --> 01:02:21,039
So that is why you settled in Gangnam?

1676
01:02:22,739 --> 01:02:24,378
He had a reason.

1677
01:02:24,379 --> 01:02:25,508
It's a Han Myong Hoe reincarnation story.

1678
01:02:25,509 --> 01:02:28,208
I'm Seo, and he's Han.

1679
01:02:28,209 --> 01:02:30,648
We have no connection whatsoever. Anyway.

1680
01:02:30,649 --> 01:02:32,388
Although the way he expressed it is different,

1681
01:02:32,389 --> 01:02:34,988
Han Myong Hoe made the same judgment as Jang Hoon.

1682
01:02:34,989 --> 01:02:36,159
This is what he said.

1683
01:02:36,919 --> 01:02:39,528
"Prince Suyang. They say that..."

1684
01:02:39,529 --> 01:02:41,489
"even when you build a thatched cottage by the roadside,"

1685
01:02:42,059 --> 01:02:44,829
"it takes three years if your intentions are not aligned."

1686
01:02:45,699 --> 01:02:48,839
"The coup is imminent. What are you hesitating about?"

1687
01:02:49,399 --> 01:02:53,269
"If you step forward, we will all follow you."

1688
01:02:54,469 --> 01:02:55,509
Prince Suyang said,

1689
01:02:56,579 --> 01:02:58,179
"I'll go and get Kim Chong So."

1690
01:02:58,709 --> 01:03:00,549
"I'll go alone."

1691
01:03:01,609 --> 01:03:03,448
They couldn't let him go alone.

1692
01:03:03,449 --> 01:03:05,319
So a servant...

1693
01:03:05,519 --> 01:03:07,548
and a group of warriors went with him.

1694
01:03:07,549 --> 01:03:08,549
(Prince Suyang was accompanied by his servant and warriors.)

1695
01:03:08,889 --> 01:03:09,959
It was a moonlit night.

1696
01:03:10,559 --> 01:03:12,158
He said at the gate, "Come here!"

1697
01:03:12,159 --> 01:03:14,488
Kim Chong So was startled.

1698
01:03:14,489 --> 01:03:15,799
"Who is there?" "It's Prince Suyang."

1699
01:03:16,259 --> 01:03:17,698
"How many are there?"

1700
01:03:17,699 --> 01:03:19,098
"It looks like he came alone..."

1701
01:03:19,099 --> 01:03:21,068
"with a servant by his side."

1702
01:03:21,069 --> 01:03:22,069
So he let his guard down.

1703
01:03:23,139 --> 01:03:24,198
That's right.

1704
01:03:24,199 --> 01:03:25,199
So...

1705
01:03:25,509 --> 01:03:27,669
- he went out with his son.
- That's right.

1706
01:03:27,839 --> 01:03:29,638
"Your Highness, what brings you here?"

1707
01:03:29,639 --> 01:03:30,639
(Kim Chong So went out with his son and greeted Prince Suyang.)

1708
01:03:31,609 --> 01:03:34,309
"There is something I'd like to tell you."

1709
01:03:34,609 --> 01:03:36,149
"But since it's hard for me to say the words,"

1710
01:03:36,749 --> 01:03:38,518
"I brought a letter."

1711
01:03:38,519 --> 01:03:40,519
"Please read it." He handed him a letter.

1712
01:03:41,389 --> 01:03:42,459
Kim Chong So...

1713
01:03:43,759 --> 01:03:45,088
couldn't read it,

1714
01:03:45,089 --> 01:03:47,459
so he turned his body to illuminate it with moonlight.

1715
01:03:47,989 --> 01:03:50,958
At that moment, Prince Suyang...

1716
01:03:50,959 --> 01:03:52,698
signaled to his servant.

1717
01:03:52,699 --> 01:03:55,299
The servant took out an iron mace...

1718
01:03:55,539 --> 01:03:58,398
and swung it at the head of Kim Chong So...

1719
01:03:58,399 --> 01:04:00,068
who was reading the letter.

1720
01:04:00,069 --> 01:04:01,069
Right.

1721
01:04:02,439 --> 01:04:03,709
Thus, he was taken out.

1722
01:04:03,939 --> 01:04:04,939
In one shot.

1723
01:04:05,179 --> 01:04:08,879
(They began the plan by removing Kim Chong So.)

1724
01:04:08,979 --> 01:04:11,179
After Kim Chong So was taken out, Prince Suyang said,

1725
01:04:12,189 --> 01:04:14,248
"The tiger hunt is over."

1726
01:04:14,249 --> 01:04:16,258
That's why his nickname was Tiger. He had the looks of a tiger.

1727
01:04:16,259 --> 01:04:17,489
Blood splattered on him.

1728
01:04:17,889 --> 01:04:20,229
With blood on his face, where did he go?

1729
01:04:20,559 --> 01:04:22,098
What did he need at this point?

1730
01:04:22,099 --> 01:04:23,099
- Authorization.
- Authorization.

1731
01:04:23,100 --> 01:04:24,399
He needed to go and receive an authorization.

1732
01:04:24,759 --> 01:04:27,528
With a group of his men, Prince Suyang...

1733
01:04:27,529 --> 01:04:29,568
went to meet Danjong.

1734
01:04:29,569 --> 01:04:31,098
Where was Danjong?

1735
01:04:31,099 --> 01:04:33,509
He was at the house of his sister, Princess Gyeonghye.

1736
01:04:33,909 --> 01:04:34,968
Prince Suyang arrived.

1737
01:04:34,969 --> 01:04:36,179
"Uncle."

1738
01:04:36,939 --> 01:04:38,409
He was covered in blood.

1739
01:04:39,579 --> 01:04:40,579
"Uncle."

1740
01:04:41,679 --> 01:04:42,679
"Your Highness."

1741
01:04:43,319 --> 01:04:47,719
"I removed the head of the rebels."

1742
01:04:48,319 --> 01:04:51,289
"I now plan to remove the remaining rebels."

1743
01:04:51,919 --> 01:04:54,159
- "Please hand over the plaque."
- If he hadn't complied...

1744
01:04:54,559 --> 01:04:57,458
The king's plaque was used...

1745
01:04:57,459 --> 01:04:59,529
to assemble the high-ranking civil servants.

1746
01:04:59,799 --> 01:05:02,298
Danjong was 13 years old.

1747
01:05:02,299 --> 01:05:04,298
- He was scared.
- What do you think he said?

1748
01:05:04,299 --> 01:05:06,968
I bet he took it out and handed it over to his uncle.

1749
01:05:06,969 --> 01:05:08,338
- He took it out and handed it over?
- Yes.

1750
01:05:08,339 --> 01:05:09,839
Tae Woo, I'm sure you remember the scene.

1751
01:05:10,479 --> 01:05:12,149
"Uncle, please take care of it."

1752
01:05:12,509 --> 01:05:13,878
- Didn't he say that?
- That's right.

1753
01:05:13,879 --> 01:05:15,549
He said, "Uncle,"

1754
01:05:16,549 --> 01:05:18,048
"please save me this once."

1755
01:05:18,049 --> 01:05:21,749
("Uncle, please save me this once." Excerpt from "Yeonryeosilgisul")

1756
01:05:21,889 --> 01:05:22,889
The king...

1757
01:05:24,489 --> 01:05:25,859
begged for his life...

1758
01:05:26,389 --> 01:05:27,829
and handed over the plaque.

1759
01:05:28,129 --> 01:05:29,129
What did it mean?

1760
01:05:29,359 --> 01:05:31,498
It was an authorization.

1761
01:05:31,499 --> 01:05:33,169
(Prince Suyang succeeded in receiving his authorization.)

1762
01:05:33,369 --> 01:05:34,969
He grabbed the plaque.

1763
01:05:35,199 --> 01:05:36,899
- At that moment, it was game over.
- It was game over.

1764
01:05:38,569 --> 01:05:40,939
The subjects were ordered to assemble early in the morning.

1765
01:05:41,139 --> 01:05:43,139
Early morning of the next day.

1766
01:05:43,409 --> 01:05:46,379
The subjects got woken up and assembled in a confused state.

1767
01:05:46,579 --> 01:05:50,479
Prince Suyang's soldiers had occupied the streets.

1768
01:05:50,649 --> 01:05:53,148
The subjects entered the palace,

1769
01:05:53,149 --> 01:05:54,718
wondering what was going on.

1770
01:05:54,719 --> 01:05:56,258
Whom did they see...

1771
01:05:56,259 --> 01:05:57,589
upon entering the palace?

1772
01:05:57,859 --> 01:05:58,859
Han Myong Hoe.

1773
01:05:59,089 --> 01:06:00,189
Hit List.

1774
01:06:01,459 --> 01:06:02,459
"Who is it?"

1775
01:06:02,999 --> 01:06:03,999
"Kim So-and-so?"

1776
01:06:04,099 --> 01:06:05,228
(Kill him.)

1777
01:06:05,229 --> 01:06:06,229
Then he was killed on the spot.

1778
01:06:06,230 --> 01:06:07,469
Was that the Hit List?

1779
01:06:08,369 --> 01:06:09,768
(With the Hit List in his hands, Han Myong Hoe began the purge.)

1780
01:06:09,769 --> 01:06:11,369
That was the Hit List.

1781
01:06:11,999 --> 01:06:14,108
So on that day,

1782
01:06:14,109 --> 01:06:15,738
- on that fateful day, - You know so much.

1783
01:06:15,739 --> 01:06:17,078
Hwangbo In got killed...

1784
01:06:17,079 --> 01:06:18,438
- at the palace.
- I see.

1785
01:06:18,439 --> 01:06:20,449
Prince Anpyeong got exiled.

1786
01:06:21,079 --> 01:06:22,079
He later got executed.

1787
01:06:22,080 --> 01:06:23,518
Prince Suyang killed his own brother.

1788
01:06:23,519 --> 01:06:25,449
(He killed his own brother under a false charge.)

1789
01:06:25,619 --> 01:06:28,248
The world turned upside down in a single day.

1790
01:06:28,249 --> 01:06:29,518
- Before sunrise.
- They had prepared...

1791
01:06:29,519 --> 01:06:30,888
- thoroughly.
- In a single day.

1792
01:06:30,889 --> 01:06:33,528
Who became powerful afterward?

1793
01:06:33,529 --> 01:06:34,988
Since everyone was dead,

1794
01:06:34,989 --> 01:06:36,859
Prince Suyang became powerful.

1795
01:06:37,299 --> 01:06:38,998
What did Prince Suyang do after becoming powerful?

1796
01:06:38,999 --> 01:06:40,768
He acknowledged achievements and handed out rewards.

1797
01:06:40,769 --> 01:06:42,269
They had a party by themselves.

1798
01:06:42,769 --> 01:06:44,698
He gave a government position to Han Myong Hoe...

1799
01:06:44,699 --> 01:06:46,108
and Kwon Ram.

1800
01:06:46,109 --> 01:06:47,208
Who else needed a position?

1801
01:06:47,209 --> 01:06:49,279
Who was the biggest contributor of the Gyeyu Coup?

1802
01:06:49,609 --> 01:06:51,008
His servant?

1803
01:06:51,009 --> 01:06:52,778
- His servant with the iron mace.
- The iron mace.

1804
01:06:52,779 --> 01:06:54,048
- It was his servant.
- Yes.

1805
01:06:54,049 --> 01:06:57,049
"Hey, Iron Mace. Is there anything you want?"

1806
01:06:57,319 --> 01:06:58,319
"My goodness."

1807
01:06:58,579 --> 01:07:01,088
"Your Highness, I'm just a servant. I don't need anything."

1808
01:07:01,089 --> 01:07:02,188
"Hey, do you have a house?"

1809
01:07:02,189 --> 01:07:03,318
"A servant doesn't have a house."

1810
01:07:03,319 --> 01:07:05,459
"I'll give you a house." He awards him Hwangbo In's house.

1811
01:07:05,689 --> 01:07:07,058
- My goodness.
- My goodness.

1812
01:07:07,059 --> 01:07:08,559
He just showered people with rewards.

1813
01:07:08,899 --> 01:07:10,099
There were four empty positions.

1814
01:07:10,459 --> 01:07:12,599
He filled the important positions with his people.

1815
01:07:12,969 --> 01:07:14,629
For two years,

1816
01:07:14,969 --> 01:07:17,098
he acted as a regency.

1817
01:07:17,099 --> 01:07:20,309
He intimidated the young Danjong to have things his way.

1818
01:07:20,539 --> 01:07:22,808
For two years, he ruled through Danjong.

1819
01:07:22,809 --> 01:07:24,439
How do you think Danjong felt?

1820
01:07:24,609 --> 01:07:25,609
Tae Woo.

1821
01:07:26,209 --> 01:07:27,578
Would you be able to live like this?

1822
01:07:27,579 --> 01:07:29,278
- Of course not.
- I'd be too scared.

1823
01:07:29,279 --> 01:07:30,279
You wouldn't be able to, right?

1824
01:07:30,949 --> 01:07:34,219
It looked like Danjong didn't have anyone on his side...

1825
01:07:35,219 --> 01:07:36,519
in this situation.

1826
01:07:37,289 --> 01:07:38,619
But one person came forward.

1827
01:07:39,589 --> 01:07:40,589
His name is here.

1828
01:07:41,089 --> 01:07:42,999
- Who is it? That's right.
- Prince Geumseong.

1829
01:07:43,559 --> 01:07:44,559
- Prince Geumseong.
- Prince Geumseong...

1830
01:07:44,560 --> 01:07:46,298
- was in "The King's Warden."
- That's right.

1831
01:07:46,299 --> 01:07:47,299
Lee Jun Hyuk.

1832
01:07:47,300 --> 01:07:48,369
That's right.

1833
01:07:48,969 --> 01:07:50,769
When Danjong was a baby,

1834
01:07:51,739 --> 01:07:53,109
King Sejong...

1835
01:07:53,509 --> 01:07:56,209
often left him at Prince Geumseong's house...

1836
01:07:57,339 --> 01:07:59,078
with about 20 soldiers.

1837
01:07:59,079 --> 01:08:01,908
There was a 15-year age gap, so Prince Geumseong raised him...

1838
01:08:01,909 --> 01:08:03,119
like a son, not a nephew.

1839
01:08:03,749 --> 01:08:05,889
Upon observing the situation, he was like,

1840
01:08:07,319 --> 01:08:08,689
"What have you done?"

1841
01:08:09,519 --> 01:08:12,059
"How will you face our older brother in the afterlife?"

1842
01:08:12,759 --> 01:08:14,489
"How will you face our father in the afterlife?"

1843
01:08:14,929 --> 01:08:16,558
"Are you insane?"

1844
01:08:16,559 --> 01:08:18,298
(Big brother, are you insane?)

1845
01:08:18,299 --> 01:08:20,629
"You even killed our brother, Prince Anpyeong."

1846
01:08:22,229 --> 01:08:23,898
"You aren't my big brother anymore."

1847
01:08:23,899 --> 01:08:25,708
I'm sure that was how he felt.

1848
01:08:25,709 --> 01:08:29,108
So Prince Geumseong built up his power...

1849
01:08:29,109 --> 01:08:30,509
to support Danjong.

1850
01:08:31,009 --> 01:08:33,079
Prince Suyang and Han Myong Hoe noticed it.

1851
01:08:33,279 --> 01:08:35,178
- Did they let him be?
- No.

1852
01:08:35,179 --> 01:08:36,648
So he got exiled.

1853
01:08:36,649 --> 01:08:37,649
(He got exiled right away.)

1854
01:08:37,650 --> 01:08:38,719
Prince Geumseong got exiled.

1855
01:08:39,089 --> 01:08:41,948
How did Danjong feel?

1856
01:08:41,949 --> 01:08:43,058
(How did Danjong feel?)

1857
01:08:43,059 --> 01:08:46,189
"Why do people who love me..."

1858
01:08:46,789 --> 01:08:48,089
"leave my side?"

1859
01:08:49,129 --> 01:08:50,228
- He was so young.
- "My mom passed away..."

1860
01:08:50,229 --> 01:08:51,328
"while birthing me."

1861
01:08:51,329 --> 01:08:52,998
My goodness.

1862
01:08:52,999 --> 01:08:54,269
"My grandma..."

1863
01:08:55,169 --> 01:08:57,269
"and grandpa who doted on me,"

1864
01:08:57,899 --> 01:08:59,439
"my dad, and my uncle..."

1865
01:09:00,009 --> 01:09:01,209
"who raised me as his own..."

1866
01:09:01,569 --> 01:09:03,079
"passed away because of me."

1867
01:09:03,679 --> 01:09:05,079
"If I surrender my power,"

1868
01:09:05,439 --> 01:09:06,909
"there'll be no more sadness."

1869
01:09:07,549 --> 01:09:08,549
"Uncle,"

1870
01:09:09,379 --> 01:09:11,249
"take the national seal."

1871
01:09:12,349 --> 01:09:13,588
("Being the late king's brother,")

1872
01:09:13,589 --> 01:09:14,818
("my uncle has always been a man of virtue.")

1873
01:09:14,819 --> 01:09:16,158
("I ask my uncle to take my heavy duty and responsibility.")

1874
01:09:16,159 --> 01:09:17,458
(Excerpt from "Annals of King Sejo")

1875
01:09:17,459 --> 01:09:19,559
Thus, he handed over the national seal.

1876
01:09:20,459 --> 01:09:24,459
When Danjong stepped down from the throne,

1877
01:09:24,859 --> 01:09:27,699
Prince Suyang became the king.

1878
01:09:27,999 --> 01:09:30,269
What was he called as the king? King Sejo.

1879
01:09:30,539 --> 01:09:31,539
King Sejo.

1880
01:09:31,839 --> 01:09:32,839
That was how it happened.

1881
01:09:32,840 --> 01:09:35,708
(Prince Suyang took the throne as King Sejo.)

1882
01:09:35,709 --> 01:09:37,638
Danjong left Gyeongbokgung Palace...

1883
01:09:37,639 --> 01:09:39,108
and went to the secondary palace, Changdeokgung Palace.

1884
01:09:39,109 --> 01:09:40,578
It's a nice palace with a lovely view.

1885
01:09:40,579 --> 01:09:41,879
He stayed there for a year.

1886
01:09:42,379 --> 01:09:45,478
In his short life, he must've been the happiest...

1887
01:09:45,479 --> 01:09:47,318
during that year.

1888
01:09:47,319 --> 01:09:48,988
- The retired king era.
- That's right.

1889
01:09:48,989 --> 01:09:51,689
The retired king. He was called the retired king.

1890
01:09:52,259 --> 01:09:53,259
But...

1891
01:09:53,629 --> 01:09:54,889
after about a year,

1892
01:09:55,659 --> 01:09:57,499
his maternal grandma visited him...

1893
01:09:58,199 --> 01:09:59,629
and told him this.

1894
01:09:59,829 --> 01:10:02,839
"Gomyeong Daesin such as Park Pyeong Nyon, Seong Sam Mun,"

1895
01:10:03,039 --> 01:10:04,898
"Ha Wi Ji, and Yi Kae..."

1896
01:10:04,899 --> 01:10:09,608
"and scholars of Jiphyeonjeon are preparing a coup..."

1897
01:10:09,609 --> 01:10:13,809
"to overthrow King Sejo and restore you to the throne."

1898
01:10:14,049 --> 01:10:18,019
(A movement to restore Danjong to the throne begins.)

1899
01:10:18,349 --> 01:10:20,719
Tae Woo, he heard those words from his grandma.

1900
01:10:21,119 --> 01:10:22,288
How do you think he felt?

1901
01:10:22,289 --> 01:10:23,859
(How did Danjong feel upon hearing those words?)

1902
01:10:24,389 --> 01:10:25,728
Although he was scared,

1903
01:10:25,729 --> 01:10:28,588
I'm sure he was relieved to know...

1904
01:10:28,589 --> 01:10:30,999
that he had people supporting him.

1905
01:10:31,499 --> 01:10:34,798
I'm sure he thought, "I think I have a chance."

1906
01:10:34,799 --> 01:10:36,268
So my guess is that he became ambitious.

1907
01:10:36,269 --> 01:10:37,438
Ambitious?

1908
01:10:37,439 --> 01:10:39,338
Consider this. Okay. It's natural to think that way.

1909
01:10:39,339 --> 01:10:41,338
It's natural to think that way. But what if they failed?

1910
01:10:41,339 --> 01:10:42,339
- Right.
- It would be the end.

1911
01:10:42,340 --> 01:10:45,338
Then he wouldn't be an accomplice,

1912
01:10:45,339 --> 01:10:46,948
but the leader of the coup.

1913
01:10:46,949 --> 01:10:48,009
Would you risk your life?

1914
01:10:48,279 --> 01:10:50,318
- He was too young to do that.
- That's right.

1915
01:10:50,319 --> 01:10:51,478
- He was young.
- I'm sure he was scared.

1916
01:10:51,479 --> 01:10:52,589
Right?

1917
01:10:53,149 --> 01:10:56,188
But he had a way to survive.

1918
01:10:56,189 --> 01:10:57,189
Can you guess what it was?

1919
01:10:57,619 --> 01:10:58,888
Telling his uncle.

1920
01:10:58,889 --> 01:11:00,088
(Telling his uncle)

1921
01:11:00,089 --> 01:11:01,189
Telling King Sejo.

1922
01:11:01,459 --> 01:11:02,958
Telling King Sejo...

1923
01:11:02,959 --> 01:11:04,798
about the Jiphyeonjeon scholar's plan...

1924
01:11:04,799 --> 01:11:06,528
would've spared his life.

1925
01:11:06,529 --> 01:11:08,128
- What would you have done?
- My goodness.

1926
01:11:08,129 --> 01:11:11,098
Why don't I remember this scene?

1927
01:11:11,099 --> 01:11:13,109
It's because you filmed the drama in snippets.

1928
01:11:14,909 --> 01:11:16,079
He didn't film the whole scene.

1929
01:11:16,209 --> 01:11:18,539
He jumped from one snippet to another.

1930
01:11:19,379 --> 01:11:20,678
- Did he tell on them?
- No way.

1931
01:11:20,679 --> 01:11:23,348
Judging by Danjong's character, he wouldn't have done that.

1932
01:11:23,349 --> 01:11:25,178
- But he was too young.
- He wouldn't have told on them.

1933
01:11:25,179 --> 01:11:26,448
He was too young.

1934
01:11:26,449 --> 01:11:27,918
He could've been driven by fear.

1935
01:11:27,919 --> 01:11:29,289
- He was young.
- He could've done it.

1936
01:11:29,689 --> 01:11:31,288
- I'm sure he was torn.
- What happened?

1937
01:11:31,289 --> 01:11:34,288
On the day of the coup, the Jiphyeonjeon scholars...

1938
01:11:34,289 --> 01:11:35,658
visited Danjong.

1939
01:11:35,659 --> 01:11:39,028
"Your Highness, please give us your authorization."

1940
01:11:39,029 --> 01:11:42,399
Then Danjong gave them an item.

1941
01:11:42,769 --> 01:11:44,098
Which item was it?

1942
01:11:44,099 --> 01:11:45,199
(Danjong gave them an item.)

1943
01:11:45,639 --> 01:11:46,839
"Here is my authorization."

1944
01:11:47,309 --> 01:11:48,309
"Go ahead."

1945
01:11:48,309 --> 01:11:49,309
He authorized the coup.

1946
01:11:49,339 --> 01:11:50,378
That's right.

1947
01:11:50,379 --> 01:11:51,738
(Danjong gave them his sword and authorized the coup.)

1948
01:11:51,739 --> 01:11:53,449
But on the day of the coup...

1949
01:11:53,579 --> 01:11:55,209
My goodness.

1950
01:11:56,449 --> 01:11:59,349
They became unlucky. Fortune wasn't on their side.

1951
01:11:59,749 --> 01:12:01,688
An anxious insider...

1952
01:12:01,689 --> 01:12:03,118
snitched on them.

1953
01:12:03,119 --> 01:12:04,858
It's always an insider.

1954
01:12:04,859 --> 01:12:06,658
- An insider snitched on them.
- An insider.

1955
01:12:06,659 --> 01:12:07,728
- Of course.
- It was an insider.

1956
01:12:07,729 --> 01:12:09,028
He decided not to overthrow King Sejo.

1957
01:12:09,029 --> 01:12:11,828
Because of that, all the Jiphyeonjeon scholars...

1958
01:12:11,829 --> 01:12:13,428
- got executed.
- Oh, no.

1959
01:12:13,429 --> 01:12:15,228
He didn't keep it a secret.

1960
01:12:15,229 --> 01:12:16,598
The surviving scholars...

1961
01:12:16,599 --> 01:12:19,708
acted like they couldn't talk, hear, or see.

1962
01:12:19,709 --> 01:12:21,169
Those six subjects did that...

1963
