He dug the ground and buried the body.

2207
01:22:06,829 --> 01:22:08,059
What did he do as soon as he buried the body?

2208
01:22:08,489 --> 01:22:09,799
- He bowed.
- After bowing,

2209
01:22:10,499 --> 01:22:12,959
the entire family ran off. They spread out everywhere.

2210
01:22:13,199 --> 01:22:15,468
They knew that they couldn't be together.

2211
01:22:15,469 --> 01:22:16,898
- All of them could be executed.
- That's right.

2212
01:22:16,899 --> 01:22:19,769
So the entire family ran off. The knowledge of where...

2213
01:22:20,009 --> 01:22:23,309
he was buried almost disappeared over time.

2214
01:22:24,079 --> 01:22:25,238
- Almost?
- Yes.

2215
01:22:25,239 --> 01:22:26,338
But it didn't.

2216
01:22:26,339 --> 01:22:27,978
- Time passed.
- Okay.

2217
01:22:27,979 --> 01:22:29,279
Time passed.

2218
01:22:29,749 --> 01:22:31,778
King Sukjong's time came.

2219
01:22:31,779 --> 01:22:32,978
(King Sukjong strengthened the royal power.)

2220
01:22:32,979 --> 01:22:34,319
To strengthen the royal power,

2221
01:22:34,789 --> 01:22:36,559
he led the Correction of History.

2222
01:22:37,489 --> 01:22:39,788
- Only a strong king can do that.
- That's right.

2223
01:22:39,789 --> 01:22:41,289
(Correction of History was done to reorganize the political orders.)

2224
01:22:41,589 --> 01:22:42,728
He told his subjects,

2225
01:22:42,729 --> 01:22:44,659
"Hey, you know about the Six Martyred Ministers."

2226
01:22:44,999 --> 01:22:46,898
"Although they were branded as rebels,"

2227
01:22:46,899 --> 01:22:48,028
"I believe they were loyal subjects."

2228
01:22:48,029 --> 01:22:49,969
"Can you do the same for me?"

2229
01:22:50,239 --> 01:22:51,839
"Learn from history."

2230
01:22:52,484 --> 01:22:54,084
"Where was Danjong buried? Over there?"

2231
01:22:54,215 --> 01:22:55,355
"Build a proper tomb."

2232
01:22:55,380 --> 01:22:56,750
Thus, Jangneung...

2233
01:22:57,509 --> 01:22:59,639
was built in King Sukjong's time.

2234
01:23:00,249 --> 01:23:01,879
"The title of Prince Nosan is nonsense."

2235
01:23:02,579 --> 01:23:05,449
"He needs a proper name. Let's call him Danjong."

2236
01:23:06,119 --> 01:23:08,219
I guess King Sukjong was charismatic.

2237
01:23:08,319 --> 01:23:11,119
- He was a very strong king.
- That's right.

2238
01:23:11,758 --> 01:23:12,988
Thus, the late king received the name of Danjong...

2239
01:23:13,329 --> 01:23:15,629
and the Six Martyred Ministers were reinstated.

2240
01:23:16,329 --> 01:23:18,829
"Eom Heung Do was a truly loyal subject."

2241
01:23:19,459 --> 01:23:20,798
"Give him the position of the Jeong Sixth Poom."

2242
01:23:20,799 --> 01:23:22,168
(Eom Heung Do, Jeong 6th Poom)

2243
01:23:22,169 --> 01:23:24,338
The Correction of History took place in King Sukjong's time,

2244
01:23:24,339 --> 01:23:26,569
two hundred and forty years after Danjong's death.

2245
01:23:27,239 --> 01:23:30,809
Since it was King Sukjong's wish,

2246
01:23:31,179 --> 01:23:32,478
his son had to continue on with the project.

2247
01:23:32,479 --> 01:23:33,809
- That's right.
- His son was King Yeongjo.

2248
01:23:34,449 --> 01:23:37,219
So King Yeongjo continued on with the project.

2249
01:23:37,749 --> 01:23:39,019
Which king came after him?

2250
01:23:39,549 --> 01:23:41,119
Crown Prince Sado passed,

2251
01:23:41,319 --> 01:23:43,919
so King Yeongjo's grandson, King Jeongjo took the throne.

2252
01:23:44,459 --> 01:23:46,958
In my opinion, Kim Jeongjo...

2253
01:23:46,959 --> 01:23:49,729
commemorated Danjong...

2254
01:23:49,899 --> 01:23:51,829
as much as King Sukjong.

2255
01:23:52,599 --> 01:23:55,169
King Jeongjo was the king of records.

2256
01:23:55,569 --> 01:23:56,699
He left many records.

2257
01:23:56,969 --> 01:23:58,338
So what did King Jeongjo do?

2258
01:23:58,339 --> 01:23:59,398
He decided to make a painting.

2259
01:23:59,399 --> 01:24:01,809
He made a painting of the place where Danjong was exiled.

2260
01:24:02,009 --> 01:24:05,278
"Cheongnyeongpo Painting" remains to this day.

2261
01:24:05,279 --> 01:24:07,308
(The place of Danjong's exile, "Cheongnyeongpo Painting")

2262
01:24:07,309 --> 01:24:09,179
What else did he record?

2263
01:24:09,349 --> 01:24:11,319
This place.

2264
01:24:12,379 --> 01:24:13,419
This place.

2265
01:24:13,719 --> 01:24:17,119
Gwanpungheon is a house, right?

2266
01:24:17,289 --> 01:24:19,819
It had a pavilion.

2267
01:24:19,989 --> 01:24:22,429
Danjong lived here for two months before his death, right?

2268
01:24:23,089 --> 01:24:25,829
Every night, he went to this pavilion. I've been here.

2269
01:24:26,329 --> 01:24:30,599
He tearfully wrote and recited a poem.

2270
01:24:30,739 --> 01:24:34,039
That poem is titled "Jagyu Poem."

2271
01:24:34,539 --> 01:24:39,039
So people began calling the pavilion Jagyuru.

2272
01:24:39,109 --> 01:24:40,449
Jagyuru.

2273
01:24:41,649 --> 01:24:43,978
(Thus, King Jeongjo preserved the tragedy of Danjong...)

2274
01:24:43,979 --> 01:24:46,019
(for the following generations through his records.)

2275
01:24:46,049 --> 01:24:49,218
Did King Jeongjo's effort get answered?

2276
01:24:49,219 --> 01:24:51,918
A mysterious happening from King Jeongjo's time...

2277
01:24:51,919 --> 01:24:53,429
is recorded in the annals.

2278
01:24:53,829 --> 01:24:54,929
Let me tell you what it is.

2279
01:24:55,659 --> 01:24:59,698
(The mystery that followed the death of the tragic king, Danjong)

2280
01:24:59,699 --> 01:25:03,199
One day, the thought of the Six Martyred Ministers...

2281
01:25:04,199 --> 01:25:05,839
suddenly entered King Jeongjo's mind.

2282
01:25:06,339 --> 01:25:08,639
So he told his subjects...

2283
01:25:08,939 --> 01:25:11,939
to give him a report on the records of the Six Martyred Ministers.

2284
01:25:12,039 --> 01:25:14,609
Not long afterward,

2285
01:25:15,079 --> 01:25:18,279
Provincial Inspector of Yeongwol, Gangwon Province,

2286
01:25:18,449 --> 01:25:20,089
sent a record.

2287
01:25:20,349 --> 01:25:23,988
King Jeongjo became shocked upon seeing this record.

2288
01:25:23,989 --> 01:25:26,019
- Why?
- Here is what it said.

2289
01:25:26,319 --> 01:25:28,359
It's in the actual annals.

2290
01:25:29,629 --> 01:25:32,529
"I'm the Provincial Inspector of Gangwon Province."

2291
01:25:33,099 --> 01:25:35,999
"I tried to restore Jagyuru."

2292
01:25:36,369 --> 01:25:39,338
Since many years had passed,

2293
01:25:39,339 --> 01:25:41,139
the pavilion was lost in a flood.

2294
01:25:41,309 --> 01:25:43,409
They didn't know where Jagyuru was located.

2295
01:25:43,879 --> 01:25:47,279
They determined the approximate location...

2296
01:25:47,379 --> 01:25:49,249
and decided to restore the pavilion there.

2297
01:25:49,749 --> 01:25:52,148
But houses were built there.

2298
01:25:52,149 --> 01:25:53,178
(Houses were built on the approximate location.)

2299
01:25:53,179 --> 01:25:55,019
He couldn't kick them out,

2300
01:25:55,849 --> 01:25:59,518
so he decided to build Jagyuru at a different location.

2301
01:25:59,519 --> 01:26:01,059
And the construction was planned.

2302
01:26:01,459 --> 01:26:02,559
That night,

2303
01:26:03,089 --> 01:26:06,359
the construction had to be halted due to thunder and lightning.

2304
01:26:07,429 --> 01:26:08,999
They tried to resume the next day,

2305
01:26:09,199 --> 01:26:10,769
but strong wind blew.

2306
01:26:11,199 --> 01:26:12,269
Did it get halted again?

2307
01:26:12,439 --> 01:26:14,468
The strong wind caused fire...

2308
01:26:14,469 --> 01:26:16,039
which spread to civilians' houses.

2309
01:26:16,809 --> 01:26:18,039
Five houses were burnt down.

2310
01:26:18,809 --> 01:26:22,249
When they removed the ashes,

2311
01:26:25,649 --> 01:26:27,519
they found the staircase of Jagyuru.

2312
01:26:29,519 --> 01:26:31,288
That was how they discovered the location.

2313
01:26:31,289 --> 01:26:32,289
(Like fate, they found the location of Jagyuru.)

2314
01:26:32,459 --> 01:26:34,088
The higher power helped them find it.

2315
01:26:34,089 --> 01:26:35,788
Mysterious things happen.

2316
01:26:35,789 --> 01:26:37,598
I can't believe it.

2317
01:26:37,599 --> 01:26:40,299
Even though it was winter, they decided to build it quickly...

2318
01:26:40,629 --> 01:26:42,569
since they were so shocked by what they found.

2319
01:26:43,329 --> 01:26:46,739
Gangwon Province was covered in snow since it was winter.

2320
01:26:47,009 --> 01:26:48,408
In December and January,

2321
01:26:48,409 --> 01:26:50,438
they couldn't get wood from anywhere.

2322
01:26:50,439 --> 01:26:52,939
They didn't know where to get the rocks.

2323
01:26:53,339 --> 01:26:55,479
Suddenly, it rained for three days.

2324
01:26:55,979 --> 01:26:58,048
Have you heard of the winter rain in Gangwon Province?

2325
01:26:58,049 --> 01:26:59,478
- It's unheard of.
- Seriously.

2326
01:26:59,479 --> 01:27:00,548
It must've melted the snow.

2327
01:27:00,549 --> 01:27:01,889
All the snow melted.

2328
01:27:02,389 --> 01:27:04,088
- It gets so cold there in winter.
- It was like that roe deer.

2329
01:27:04,089 --> 01:27:05,118
- That's right.
- I'm from Gangwon Province.

2330
01:27:05,119 --> 01:27:06,388
Since the river melted,

2331
01:27:06,389 --> 01:27:08,029
they could get logs from the upper bank.

2332
01:27:08,929 --> 01:27:12,099
Since the mud was slippery, they could move rocks easily.

2333
01:27:12,299 --> 01:27:15,799
They built the foundation on the spot they were guided to.

2334
01:27:16,229 --> 01:27:19,039
The pillars were erected in February.

2335
01:27:19,269 --> 01:27:21,169
What King Jeongjo said...

2336
01:27:21,609 --> 01:27:24,139
upon reading the report is in the annals.

2337
01:27:24,579 --> 01:27:27,449
"It's strange. It's truly strange."

2338
01:27:27,849 --> 01:27:30,419
"The day I suddenly thought of the Six Martyred Ministers..."

2339
01:27:30,679 --> 01:27:32,949
"and received a report..."

2340
01:27:33,619 --> 01:27:37,159
"was the day the pillars were erected."

2341
01:27:39,619 --> 01:27:40,928
("It's strange. How could one say...")

2342
01:27:40,929 --> 01:27:42,288
("that there is a right time to restore a fallen pavilion?")

2343
01:27:42,289 --> 01:27:43,598
("The day an envoy came back and gave a report...")

2344
01:27:43,599 --> 01:27:44,958
("was the day the pillars of Jagyuru were erected.")

2345
01:27:44,959 --> 01:27:46,198
("It'd be impossible to call it coincidental and common.")

2346
01:27:46,199 --> 01:27:47,429
(Excerpt from "Annals of King Jeongjo")

2347
01:27:47,729 --> 01:27:49,868
- "From now on, report..."
- This is so interesting.

2348
01:27:49,869 --> 01:27:51,969
"everything that happens..."

2349
01:27:52,069 --> 01:27:53,469
"in Yeongwol, Gangwon Province,"

2350
01:27:54,069 --> 01:27:57,079
"regardless of the gravity." He gave that order.

2351
01:27:57,779 --> 01:27:59,579
Then one month passed.

2352
01:27:59,839 --> 01:28:01,408
When he was done lighting an incense stick...

2353
01:28:01,409 --> 01:28:02,949
for the Crown Prince Sado,

2354
01:28:03,149 --> 01:28:06,919
a sudden thought made him call over the Provincial Inspector.

2355
01:28:07,549 --> 01:28:09,488
"Are you holding the memorial services properly?"

2356
01:28:09,489 --> 01:28:10,889
"Yes, we are."

2357
01:28:10,959 --> 01:28:12,389
Chae Che Gong who was next to him said...

2358
01:28:14,789 --> 01:28:16,259
something unbelievable.

2359
01:28:17,329 --> 01:28:18,399
"Your Highness,"

2360
01:28:19,799 --> 01:28:24,169
"there was something I couldn't tell you."

2361
01:28:25,099 --> 01:28:27,809
"Last night, at the pavilion,"

2362
01:28:28,239 --> 01:28:31,379
"red fen fire was observed."

2363
01:28:31,709 --> 01:28:34,779
"It circled the pavilion 2, 3 times..."

2364
01:28:35,179 --> 01:28:38,019
"and headed straight to Jangneung."

2365
01:28:38,549 --> 01:28:41,248
The tomb keeper ran out because he thought it was a fire.

2366
01:28:41,249 --> 01:28:45,859
All the villagers thought it was an eerie sight.

2367
01:28:47,429 --> 01:28:48,458
King Jeongjo said,

2368
01:28:48,459 --> 01:28:49,459
(King Jeongjo's reaction upon receiving the report)

2369
01:28:49,959 --> 01:28:51,029
"They say..."

2370
01:28:52,529 --> 01:28:55,769
"those who have lived comfortably pass away in peace."

2371
01:28:56,569 --> 01:29:00,338
"But those who passed away with resentment in their hearts..."

2372
01:29:00,339 --> 01:29:03,238
"cause eerie events after their deaths."

2373
01:29:03,239 --> 01:29:05,909
"That must be the reason behind what happened."

2374
01:29:06,309 --> 01:29:09,779
"Aren't there descendants of the Six Martyred Ministers?"

2375
01:29:10,049 --> 01:29:11,179
"Yes, there are."

2376
01:29:11,949 --> 01:29:15,289
"Park Ki Jeong is the descendant of Park Pyeong Nyon."

2377
01:29:17,259 --> 01:29:19,519
"Park Ki Jeong has the blood of a loyal subject."

2378
01:29:19,759 --> 01:29:21,889
"Appoint him as the magistrate of Yeongwol, Gangwon Province."

2379
01:29:22,089 --> 01:29:25,298
"And hold the memorial services with care."

2380
01:29:25,299 --> 01:29:27,429
He gave that order.

2381
01:29:29,429 --> 01:29:32,298
King Jeongjo commemorated Danjong that way.

2382
01:29:32,299 --> 01:29:33,609
(Time has passed, but people continue to commemorate Danjong.)

2383
01:29:33,869 --> 01:29:35,339
It has been...

2384
01:29:35,939 --> 01:29:38,909
six hundred years since Danjong's lonely death.

2385
01:29:39,539 --> 01:29:43,079
Danjong's innocence was proven by King Sukjong...

2386
01:29:43,679 --> 01:29:45,319
and King Jeongjo.

2387
01:29:45,849 --> 01:29:49,688
In 2026, who is the king of Korea?

2388
01:29:49,689 --> 01:29:51,558
- The people.
- The people.

2389
01:29:51,559 --> 01:29:54,689
- The people.
- Now, we're the owners of Korea.

2390
01:29:55,029 --> 01:30:00,229
So we'll honor him and commemorate him once more.

2391
01:30:02,669 --> 01:30:06,039
Many dramas have told Danjong's story.

2392
01:30:06,699 --> 01:30:09,039
Min Woo and Tae Woo were in such dramas.

2393
01:30:09,409 --> 01:30:12,878
But those dramas didn't become so big.

2394
01:30:12,879 --> 01:30:17,878
So why do Koreans miss Danjong so much at this point in time?

2395
01:30:17,879 --> 01:30:20,149
I think there are two reasons. Firstly,

2396
01:30:20,389 --> 01:30:23,919
the director's view was exceptional.

2397
01:30:23,944 --> 01:30:26,174
In Min Woo and Tae Woo's dramas,

2398
01:30:26,959 --> 01:30:29,528
Danjong was painted...

2399
01:30:29,529 --> 01:30:32,059
as a passive and pitiful being who surrendered to his fate.

2400
01:30:32,429 --> 01:30:34,269
But the recent movie...

2401
01:30:34,369 --> 01:30:38,038
painted him as an active man...

2402
01:30:38,039 --> 01:30:41,438
who tried to fight his fate.

2403
01:30:41,439 --> 01:30:43,108
And who was behind him?

2404
01:30:43,109 --> 01:30:44,378
- Eom Heung Do.
- The villagers.

2405
01:30:44,379 --> 01:30:46,739
- Eom Heung Do and the civilians.
- Civilians.

2406
01:30:46,839 --> 01:30:49,308
The character who tried to fight his fate...

2407
01:30:49,309 --> 01:30:52,819
with the support of the civilians...

2408
01:30:52,979 --> 01:30:56,189
moved the viewers' hearts.

2409
01:30:56,349 --> 01:30:57,419
Secondly,

2410
01:30:58,119 --> 01:31:01,059
I believe the movie suited the spirit of the age.

2411
01:31:01,729 --> 01:31:04,359
The unjustified and unfair power...

2412
01:31:06,059 --> 01:31:08,999
destroyed a weak person's life.

2413
01:31:09,169 --> 01:31:11,599
Back in the day, a select few had vested rights.

2414
01:31:11,839 --> 01:31:14,069
Now, the civilians have them.

2415
01:31:14,409 --> 01:31:17,878
The spirit of the age which involves safeguarding the helpless...

2416
01:31:17,879 --> 01:31:20,239
and fighting injustice...

2417
01:31:20,549 --> 01:31:24,019
led to a movie that painted Danjong...

2418
01:31:24,319 --> 01:31:28,389
under a new light, in my opinion.

2419
01:31:30,249 --> 01:31:31,459
- Guys.
- Yes.

2420
01:31:31,919 --> 01:31:34,689
The forgotten history repeats itself.

2421
01:31:34,889 --> 01:31:39,259
So that such a tragic event doesn't happen again,

2422
01:31:39,434 --> 01:31:42,904
all of us should remember it by heart.

2423
01:31:45,339 --> 01:31:46,339
How cool.

2424
01:31:47,239 --> 01:31:50,169
Watching the movie with this knowledge will be so fun.

2425
01:31:50,979 --> 01:31:52,708
This will be a good summary for those...

2426
01:31:52,709 --> 01:31:55,679
- who have watched the movie.
- It was incredible.

2427
01:31:55,879 --> 01:31:56,908
How was it today?

2428
01:31:56,909 --> 01:31:59,079
Tae Woo, how did it feel to be on the show?

2429
01:31:59,349 --> 01:32:02,289
This school has an incredible class.

2430
01:32:03,219 --> 01:32:04,719
I want to transfer to this school.

2431
01:32:05,119 --> 01:32:06,619
You can't do that. There is no opening.

2432
01:32:07,889 --> 01:32:09,859
Coming here and filming the show...

2433
01:32:10,329 --> 01:32:12,929
was incredibly fun. Thank you so much.

2434
01:32:12,959 --> 01:32:16,329
And I really enjoyed Mr. Seol Min Seok's...

2435
01:32:16,369 --> 01:32:18,668
amazing lecture. Thank you.

2436
01:32:18,669 --> 01:32:19,999
- All right.
- Thank you.

2437
01:32:20,509 --> 01:32:21,538
Min Seok.

2438
01:32:21,539 --> 01:32:24,539
I visited Men on a Mission because I heard that it'd be...

2439
01:32:24,909 --> 01:32:26,709
a special on Danjong.

2440
01:32:26,979 --> 01:32:30,079
The members were so serious about learning the history.

2441
01:32:30,349 --> 01:32:31,979
If there are teachers who are uncertain...

2442
01:32:32,879 --> 01:32:36,048
about visiting the show,

2443
01:32:36,049 --> 01:32:38,589
I want to remind them that the members have various facets.

2444
01:32:38,759 --> 01:32:40,459
They'll be able to teach a class comfortably.

2445
01:32:40,889 --> 01:32:42,558
Visit the show right away.

2446
01:32:42,559 --> 01:32:44,299
- That's right.
- Thank you.

2447
01:32:44,659 --> 01:32:46,498
- We won't let you down.
- We won't disappoint you.

2448
01:32:46,499 --> 01:32:48,628
We won't hurt you. Come.

2449
01:32:48,629 --> 01:32:50,668
You'll continue to give amazing lectures and performances.

2450
01:32:50,669 --> 01:32:54,009
- We'll root for you!
- We'll root for you!

2451
01:32:55,109 --> 01:32:57,009
(My sister, come on in.)

2452
01:32:57,309 --> 01:32:59,809
(Special transfer student, Kim Shin Young)

2453
01:33:00,039 --> 01:33:01,049
(Jumong!)

2454
